56
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:01,962
- Blink! No!
- (MOANS)

57
00:07:02,338 --> 00:07:03,631
(PANTING)

58
00:07:07,885 --> 00:07:09,053
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

59
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:22,775
(ROARING)

60
00:07:23,484 --> 00:07:24,610
(YELLS)

61
00:07:29,198 --> 00:07:30,366
(GROWLS)

62
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:48,134
(ROARING)

63
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:50,553
Too late, assholes.

64
00:08:08,946 --> 00:08:10,072
(MAN SOBBING)

65
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:11,699
Don't move,
you mutant scum!

66
00:08:12,366 --> 00:08:13,742
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

67
00:08:15,411 --> 00:08:16,579
No!

68
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:20,166
Flat on the ground,
hands behind your head!

69
00:08:20,249 --> 00:08:21,917
(MAN SCREAMING)

70
00:08:23,419 --> 00:08:24,920
(WOMAN SOBBING)

71
00:08:25,087 --> 00:08:27,715
PROFESSOR X:
 So few of us left.

72
00:08:31,093 --> 00:08:32,136
KITTY:  Professor?

73
00:08:33,429 --> 00:08:34,680
I've found them.

74
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:40,227
(POWERING UP)

75
00:09:28,442 --> 00:09:29,568
(LIGHTER CLICKS)

76
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:08,107
BOBBY: Professor!

77
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,360
- Bobby.
- Hey, Storm.

78
00:10:12,486 --> 00:10:13,529
Hey, kid.

79
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:17,074
KITTY: Professor,
you made it.

80
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:31,755
Whenever the Sentinels attack,
Warpath spots them...

81
00:10:32,423 --> 00:10:34,300
then I send Bishop
back to warn us

82
00:10:34,383 --> 00:10:36,135
of the attack
before it happens.

83
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:38,804
Blink scouts
the next site...

84
00:10:39,555 --> 00:10:41,890
and then we leave before they
ever know we were there.

85
00:10:42,057 --> 00:10:44,685
Because...
we never were.

86
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:46,687
What do you mean
you were never there?

87
00:10:46,854 --> 00:10:48,480
She projects
Bishop back in time

88
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:49,898
a few days to
warn the others...

89
00:10:50,065 --> 00:10:51,692
of the coming attack.

90
00:10:51,859 --> 00:10:53,986
So she sends
Bishop back in time?

91
00:10:54,111 --> 00:10:56,780
No, just his consciousness,
into his younger self.

92
00:10:56,947 --> 00:10:58,198
His younger body.

93
00:10:58,991 --> 00:11:00,159
Wow.

94
00:11:00,868 --> 00:11:03,954
This might just work,
Charles.

95
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,248
What might work?

96
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:09,793
The Sentinel program
was originally

97
00:11:09,877 --> 00:11:12,046
conceived by
Doctor Bolivar Trask.

98
00:11:12,379 --> 00:11:16,842
In the early '70s, he was one of the
world's leading weapons designers.

99
00:11:17,092 --> 00:11:21,305
 But, covertly, he had begun
experimenting on mutants...

100
00:11:21,472 --> 00:11:24,641
 using their gifts
to fuel his own research.

101
00:11:24,808 --> 00:11:26,185
TRASK: This is extraordinary.

102
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:29,563
PROFESSOR X:  There was one mutant who
had discovered what he was doing.

103
00:11:29,772 --> 00:11:34,735
A mutant with the ability to
transform herself into anyone.

104
00:11:35,235 --> 00:11:36,653
Mystique.

105
00:11:37,529 --> 00:11:39,615
PROFESSOR X:
 I knew her as Raven.

106
00:11:39,823 --> 00:11:41,241
We met when
we were children,

107
00:11:41,325 --> 00:11:43,160
grew up together.

108
00:11:44,036 --> 00:11:45,829
She was like
a sister to me.

109
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:47,873
I tried to help her...

110
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:51,585
but only succeeded
in driving her away.

111
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:55,172
She hunted Trask
across the world.

112
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:58,801
And at the Paris
Peace Accords in 1973,

113
00:11:58,884 --> 00:12:00,135
 after the Vietnam War...

114
00:12:00,969 --> 00:12:02,346
 she found Trask...

115
00:12:05,432 --> 00:12:06,975
- and killed him.
- (GUNSHOT)

116
00:12:13,148 --> 00:12:14,858
 It was the first
time she killed.

117
00:12:14,983 --> 00:12:16,568
It wasn't her last.

118
00:12:16,735 --> 00:12:20,489
But killing Trask did not have
the outcome she expected.

119
00:12:20,614 --> 00:12:22,408
It only persuaded
the government

120
00:12:22,491 --> 00:12:24,660
of the need
for his program.

121
00:12:24,868 --> 00:12:27,037
- (GASPS)
PROFESSOR X: They captured her that day...

122
00:12:27,204 --> 00:12:29,998
tortured her,
experimented on her.

123
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:33,502
 In her DNA,
they discovered the secrets

124
00:12:33,585 --> 00:12:35,379
 to her powers of
transformation.

125
00:12:35,546 --> 00:12:37,589
 It gave them
the key they needed...

126
00:12:37,714 --> 00:12:41,718
 to create weapons that could
adapt to any mutant power.

127
00:12:42,177 --> 00:12:44,138
 And in less than 50 years...

128
00:12:44,304 --> 00:12:46,473
 the machines that
have destroyed...

129
00:12:46,598 --> 00:12:50,394
 - so many of our kind were created.  
- (LOW GROWL)

130
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:54,189
But it all started
that day in 1973...

131
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:56,066
the day she first killed.

132
00:12:56,358 --> 00:12:58,277
The day she truly became...

133
00:12:58,402 --> 00:12:59,862
Mystique.

134
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:03,240
You want to
go back there.

135
00:13:03,407 --> 00:13:06,702
If I can get to her,
stop the assassination...

136
00:13:06,827 --> 00:13:08,245
keep her out
of their hands...

137
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:11,832
then we can stop the Sentinels
from ever being born.

138
00:13:11,957 --> 00:13:15,210
And end this war
before it ever begins.

139
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:22,259
Uh, I can send someone
back a couple weeks.

140
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,178
Maybe a month.

141
00:13:24,261 --> 00:13:27,556
But you're talking about
going back decades.

142
00:13:27,639 --> 00:13:30,517
You have the most powerful brain
in the world, Professor...

143
00:13:31,226 --> 00:13:34,897
but the mind can only stretch
so far before it snaps.

144
00:13:35,397 --> 00:13:38,484
It would rip you apart.
I'm sorry.

145
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:40,819
No one could
survive that trip.

146
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:44,239
What if someone's mind
has a way of snapping back?

147
00:13:45,741 --> 00:13:48,911
What if someone can heal as
fast as they're ripped apart?

148
00:14:13,769 --> 00:14:15,103
STORM: Okay, spread out.

149
00:14:15,270 --> 00:14:17,439
BISHOP: Take your positions.

150
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,485
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

151
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:34,039
So I wake up in my younger
body, God knows where.

152
00:14:34,122 --> 00:14:35,290
Then what?

153
00:14:35,457 --> 00:14:38,460
You'll need to go to
my house and find me.

154
00:14:38,627 --> 00:14:41,213
Convince me
of all of this.

155
00:14:41,296 --> 00:14:43,048
Won't you be able
to just read my mind?

156
00:14:43,131 --> 00:14:46,343
I didn't have my
powers in 1973.

157
00:14:46,677 --> 00:14:49,263
Logan, you're going
to have to do for me

158
00:14:49,346 --> 00:14:50,847
what I once did for you.

159
00:14:51,056 --> 00:14:53,809
Lead me, guide me.

160
00:14:54,142 --> 00:14:56,436
I was a very
different man then.

161
00:14:56,562 --> 00:14:58,730
- You'll have to be patient with me.
- (LOGAN SCOFFS)

162
00:14:59,481 --> 00:15:01,984
Patience is
my strongest suit.

163
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:03,235
You'll need me as well.

164
00:15:03,318 --> 00:15:04,361
What?

165
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:07,281
After Mystique left Charles,
she came with me...

166
00:15:07,364 --> 00:15:10,492
and I set her on
a dangerous path.

167
00:15:10,826 --> 00:15:12,119
A darker path.

168
00:15:12,202 --> 00:15:14,871
It's going to take the two
of us, side by side...

169
00:15:14,955 --> 00:15:17,666
at a time when we couldn't
be further apart.

170
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:22,337
Great.

171
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:24,840
So where do I find you?

172
00:15:25,173 --> 00:15:26,675
Well, it's complicated.

173
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:31,763
Basically, your body
will go to sleep

174
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:34,016
while your mind
travels back in time.

175
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:35,220
As long as
you're back there,

176
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:38,395
past and present will
continue to coexist.

177
00:15:38,854 --> 00:15:40,188
But once you wake up...

178
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:44,234
whatever you've done will
take hold and become history.

179
00:15:44,526 --> 00:15:47,446
And for the rest of us, it will
be the only history that we know.

180
00:15:47,529 --> 00:15:50,907
It will be like the last
50 years never happened.

181
00:15:51,366 --> 00:15:53,577
And this world,
and this war...

182
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:57,122
the only person who will
remember it is you.

183
00:15:58,999 --> 00:16:00,000
All right, Logan...

184
00:16:00,083 --> 00:16:01,543
I need you to
clear your head

185
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,295
and to stay as
calm as possible.

186
00:16:03,378 --> 00:16:04,880
What? What do you mean?

187
00:16:04,963 --> 00:16:07,341
If your mind gets rocky, it will
be harder for me to hold you...

188
00:16:07,424 --> 00:16:09,801
and you could start to slip
between past and future.

189
00:16:09,885 --> 00:16:11,887
What if I need to
get a little rocky?

190
00:16:13,013 --> 00:16:14,306
Think peaceful thoughts?

191
00:16:14,389 --> 00:16:17,309
Peaceful thoughts...
Do you have any good news?

192
00:16:17,476 --> 00:16:20,103
Well, you don't really age,

193
00:16:20,187 --> 00:16:21,587
so you'll pretty
much look the same.

194
00:16:22,397 --> 00:16:24,399
BOBBY: You won't have
much time in the past.

195
00:16:24,483 --> 00:16:26,026
The Sentinels
will find us.

196
00:16:26,109 --> 00:16:27,444
They always do.

197
00:16:27,611 --> 00:16:29,237
And this time,
we won't be able to run.

198
00:16:29,404 --> 00:16:30,947
We'll have no escape.

199
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:34,284
This is our last chance.

200
00:16:34,743 --> 00:16:36,662
You really think
this will work?

201
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:38,580
I have faith in him.

202
00:16:38,747 --> 00:16:40,667
MAGNETO: It's not him I'm
worried about, it's us.

203
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:42,250
We were young...

204
00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:43,919
we didn't know
any better.

205
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:47,422
We will now.

206
00:16:48,465 --> 00:16:49,800
See you all soon.

207
00:16:49,966 --> 00:16:51,927
This might sting a little.

208
00:16:55,430 --> 00:16:57,265
(SCREAMING)

209
00:17:09,611 --> 00:17:11,613
(SOFT '70s SONG PLAYING)

210
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:44,521
 The first time

211
00:17:47,315 --> 00:17:50,736
 Ever I saw your face

212
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:52,112
(WATERBED SLOSHING)

213
00:17:52,195 --> 00:17:53,405
Whoa.

214
00:17:57,617 --> 00:18:01,913
 I thought the sun

215
00:18:03,457 --> 00:18:04,499
 Rose in your eyes

216
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:05,834
(GRUNTS)

217
00:18:06,334 --> 00:18:07,878
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

218
00:18:14,634 --> 00:18:20,182
 And the moon
and the stars

219
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:28,106
 Were the gifts you gave

220
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:29,649
LOGAN: Holy shit.

221
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:33,528
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

222
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:39,326
It worked.

223
00:18:43,872 --> 00:18:45,123
Hey, what's going on?

224
00:18:45,207 --> 00:18:47,334
Gwen, get dressed.
LOGAN: Who the hell are you?

225
00:18:47,417 --> 00:18:48,543
Hey, I don't know
what's going on.

226
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:49,961
You're supposed to be

227
00:18:50,045 --> 00:18:51,254
guarding the boss's daughter,
not screwing her.

228
00:18:51,379 --> 00:18:53,256
Well, I didn't
sleep with her.

229
00:18:53,381 --> 00:18:55,050
MAN: No?
- No.

230
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:58,470
I mean, yes, I slept
with her many times.

231
00:18:58,553 --> 00:18:59,805
Jimmy!

232
00:18:59,888 --> 00:19:02,390
That wasn't me.
That was the old me.

233
00:19:02,474 --> 00:19:05,143
I just got here
20 seconds ago.

234
00:19:05,227 --> 00:19:06,228
MAN: Really?

235
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:07,312
Then what happened
to your clothes?

236
00:19:07,395 --> 00:19:08,939
My-- Oh.

237
00:19:09,564 --> 00:19:10,982
Would you believe
me if I told you

238
00:19:11,066 --> 00:19:12,567
I was sent here
from the future?

239
00:19:12,692 --> 00:19:14,069
Huh?

240
00:19:14,152 --> 00:19:15,278
(CHUCKLES)

241
00:19:15,403 --> 00:19:16,905
- Get out of here, sweetheart.
- Yeah.

242
00:19:16,947 --> 00:19:18,824
- We're gonna take care of this comedian.
LOGAN: No, you're not.

243
00:19:18,907 --> 00:19:21,117
You're gonna give me the keys to
your car and some money for gas...

244
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:22,410
or you're gonna wake
up in the hospital.

245
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:24,287
Trust me, I know how
these things play out.

246
00:19:24,412 --> 00:19:25,997
Oh. Because you're
from the future?

247
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:27,123
No.

248
00:19:27,666 --> 00:19:28,917
Because of these.

249
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:32,712
MAN: What the hell?
- (GRUNTING)

250
00:19:33,004 --> 00:19:34,005
(GUNSHOTS)

251
00:19:36,508 --> 00:19:39,177
(GROANS)
God damn it!

252
00:19:39,386 --> 00:19:40,804
(GRUNTS)

253
00:19:40,887 --> 00:19:42,681
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

254
00:19:42,764 --> 00:19:43,765
(BULLETS CLATTERING)

255
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:46,685
(GRUNTING)

256
00:19:51,273 --> 00:19:52,274
- (GUNSHOT)
- (YELLS)

257
00:19:52,732 --> 00:19:53,733
(GRUNTING)

258
00:19:59,114 --> 00:20:01,116
Peaceful thoughts.

259
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:02,576
(PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

260
00:20:16,756 --> 00:20:19,477
SENATOR BRICKMAN: We are reviewing
all of our defense expenditures...

261
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:21,595
and all the black books
are being opened.

262
00:20:21,761 --> 00:20:25,682
We can't support a weapon
that targets our own citizens.

263
00:20:25,849 --> 00:20:27,475
If these mutants,
as you describe...

264
00:20:28,018 --> 00:20:29,978
are already
living among us...

265
00:20:30,145 --> 00:20:31,980
then they are living
here peacefully.

266
00:20:32,147 --> 00:20:33,732
PARKER: We haven't had an
incident in over 10 years.

267
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:35,150
After what happened
in Cuba?

268
00:20:35,275 --> 00:20:36,610
PARKER: That was
never confirmed.

269
00:20:36,776 --> 00:20:38,987
We have very real
enemies out there...

270
00:20:39,154 --> 00:20:40,488
the Russians, the Chinese.

271
00:20:40,572 --> 00:20:43,658
We are talking about
a tenth of a tenth...

272
00:20:43,825 --> 00:20:45,869
of a tenth
of our population.

273
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:48,371
Allow me to read
something to you.

274
00:20:48,455 --> 00:20:49,581
Please.

275
00:20:49,664 --> 00:20:52,542
This was acquired by
our friends at the CIA.

276
00:20:52,709 --> 00:20:53,960
It's a dissertation...

277
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:57,797
written by a mutant
at Oxford University.

278
00:20:58,590 --> 00:20:59,966
And I quote...

279
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:02,302
"To Homo Neanderthalensis...

280
00:21:02,469 --> 00:21:04,679
"his mutant cousin,
Homo Sapiens..."

281
00:21:05,138 --> 00:21:06,473
which is us...

282
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,642
"was an aberration.

283
00:21:08,808 --> 00:21:11,937
"The arrival of the mutated
human species, Homo Sapiens...

284
00:21:12,103 --> 00:21:16,441
"was followed by the immediate
extinction of their less evolved kin."

285
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:18,068
Well...

286
00:21:18,652 --> 00:21:23,073
Now, we are
the Neanderthal.

287
00:21:23,239 --> 00:21:24,991
Speak for yourself,
Dr. Trask.

288
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:26,618
- (ALL LAUGHING)
- (CHUCKLES)

289
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:29,871
You know, when you sent our
soldiers to Vietnam...

290
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:31,665
without the weapons they
needed to win the war...

291
00:21:31,831 --> 00:21:33,750
you underestimated
your enemy.

292
00:21:33,875 --> 00:21:37,212
(CHUCKLING) You do that
with this enemy...

293
00:21:37,295 --> 00:21:38,463
Mmm...

294
00:21:38,546 --> 00:21:41,549
and it won't be some border
skirmish halfway around the world.

295
00:21:41,716 --> 00:21:43,885
This time, the war will
be for our streets...

296
00:21:44,052 --> 00:21:46,262
our cities, our homes...

297
00:21:46,429 --> 00:21:50,475
and by the time you see the
need for my program...

298
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:52,936
it will be too late...

299
00:21:53,103 --> 00:21:57,732
and you will have lost
two wars in one lifetime.

300
00:22:00,652 --> 00:22:02,779
We are sorry,
Dr. Trask...

301
00:22:03,196 --> 00:22:05,532
but your
Sentinel Program...

302
00:22:06,157 --> 00:22:08,159
it ain't gonna fly.

303
00:22:08,410 --> 00:22:10,245
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

304
00:22:20,755 --> 00:22:21,923
Can I help you, Colonel?

305
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:24,300
Just here to give our
boys a proper send-off.

306
00:22:24,426 --> 00:22:27,762
I'm sorry, sir, but we have orders.
This is a quarantined area.

307
00:22:27,929 --> 00:22:29,931
Stand aside, soldier.

308
00:22:30,098 --> 00:22:31,975
That's an order.

309
00:22:41,109 --> 00:22:42,110
SOLDIER: Atten-hut!

310
00:22:43,111 --> 00:22:44,195
At ease.
(CLEARS THROAT)

311
00:23:07,635 --> 00:23:08,887
What is all this?

312
00:23:08,970 --> 00:23:10,555
Lab reports,
blood tests.

313
00:23:10,972 --> 00:23:12,390
It's all getting packed up
and shipped back.

314
00:23:12,474 --> 00:23:13,600
Where is it going?

315
00:23:13,683 --> 00:23:14,726
Same place they are.

316
00:23:15,518 --> 00:23:16,811
Trask Industries.

317
00:23:18,354 --> 00:23:19,939
STRYKER:
Let's go, gentlemen.

318
00:23:20,023 --> 00:23:22,317
I'm taking you out
of this shit show.

319
00:23:22,484 --> 00:23:24,319
HAVOK: Shipping home?

320
00:23:25,361 --> 00:23:26,529
Not just yet.

321
00:23:27,238 --> 00:23:28,740
What are you doing
with those?

322
00:23:28,823 --> 00:23:30,617
Something to make the ride
a little smoother.

323
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:33,203
I'm transferring you
to a private facility...

324
00:23:33,828 --> 00:23:35,705
where we can run
a few more tests.

325
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:39,950
(COLONEL SANDERS
CLEARS THROAT)

326
00:23:41,336 --> 00:23:42,754
Your men
are not military.

327
00:23:44,089 --> 00:23:45,090
Private outfit.

328
00:23:45,548 --> 00:23:47,050
We're authorized
to remand these men.

329
00:23:47,258 --> 00:23:48,259
Hmm.

330
00:23:51,679 --> 00:23:53,431
These troops
are going home.

331
00:23:53,598 --> 00:23:57,602
Well, Colonel, I don't believe you
have jurisdiction in this matter.

332
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:00,855
I'm afraid I do, son.

333
00:24:01,022 --> 00:24:02,148
I'm sorry, who are you?

334
00:24:02,774 --> 00:24:04,442
The question is,
Major...

335
00:24:08,696 --> 00:24:09,697
...who are you?

336
00:24:12,033 --> 00:24:13,034
(GRUNTS)

337
00:24:15,036 --> 00:24:16,037
(GRUNTS)

338
00:24:16,371 --> 00:24:17,372
(GRUNTS)

339
00:24:18,248 --> 00:24:19,374
(GRUNTS)

340
00:24:22,919 --> 00:24:23,920
(GROANS)

341
00:24:38,059 --> 00:24:39,060
(SCREAMS)

342
00:24:40,728 --> 00:24:41,729
(GRUNTS)

343
00:24:49,988 --> 00:24:51,072
(CHOKING)

344
00:24:55,118 --> 00:24:56,202
Raven!

345
00:24:56,619 --> 00:24:57,996
That's not my name.

346
00:25:01,416 --> 00:25:02,917
(GRUNTING)

347
00:25:03,585 --> 00:25:05,587
(EXHALES SHARPLY)
I had that.

348
00:25:05,753 --> 00:25:06,838
I know.

349
00:25:08,673 --> 00:25:10,633
Let's move out.
Come on, let's go.

350
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:11,968
HAVOK: Where's Erik?

351
00:25:12,135 --> 00:25:13,219
I'm on my own now.

352
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:17,974
Let's go! Move it!

353
00:25:18,183 --> 00:25:20,268
(SOLDIERS
YELLING INDISTINCTLY)

354
00:25:36,743 --> 00:25:38,286
Hold that plane!

355
00:25:38,786 --> 00:25:41,623
Wouldn't wanna leave these boys
in this godforsaken country.

356
00:25:41,789 --> 00:25:42,790
SOLDIER: Yes, sir.

357
00:25:43,458 --> 00:25:45,335
You're not coming
with us, are you?

358
00:25:45,793 --> 00:25:47,170
My war's not over.

359
00:25:47,337 --> 00:25:48,880
The enemy is
still out there.

360
00:26:12,153 --> 00:26:14,072
The four privates,
where did they go?

361
00:26:14,239 --> 00:26:16,074
They were headed
towards the tarmac.

362
00:27:14,841 --> 00:27:16,217
Can I help you?

363
00:27:16,634 --> 00:27:19,095
Uh... Yeah, what
happened to the school?

364
00:27:19,262 --> 00:27:22,223
The school's been shut for years.
Are you a parent?

365
00:27:22,307 --> 00:27:25,018
(SCOFFS) I sure as hell
hope not. Who are you?

366
00:27:25,226 --> 00:27:27,228
I'm Hank. Hank McCoy.

367
00:27:27,353 --> 00:27:29,397
I look after the house now.

368
00:27:30,189 --> 00:27:31,441
You're Beast?

369
00:27:31,524 --> 00:27:33,943
Look at you. I guess
you're a late bloomer.

370
00:27:34,068 --> 00:27:35,194
I don't know what
you're talking about,

371
00:27:35,278 --> 00:27:36,863
but I'm gonna have
to ask you to leave.

372
00:27:37,113 --> 00:27:38,698
- (GRUNTS)
- So where's the Professor?

373
00:27:38,781 --> 00:27:40,033
There's no professor here.

374
00:27:40,116 --> 00:27:42,243
You're pretty strong
for a scrawny kid.

375
00:27:42,410 --> 00:27:44,704
You sure there's not
a little Beast in there?

376
00:27:44,787 --> 00:27:46,497
- No, he's not here.
- Come on, Beast.

377
00:27:46,581 --> 00:27:48,041
- Come on, Beastie.
- No.

378
00:27:48,249 --> 00:27:49,876
(GRUNTS) Hey!

379
00:27:51,419 --> 00:27:52,628
I said
the school's closed.

380
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:54,834
- You need to leave.
- Not until I see the Professor.

381
00:27:54,922 --> 00:27:57,383
There's no professor here,
I told you that.

382
00:27:57,508 --> 00:28:01,054
Look, kid. You and I are
gonna be good friends.

383
00:28:01,512 --> 00:28:03,222
- (GRUNTS)
- (GROANS)

384
00:28:03,306 --> 00:28:05,266
You just don't know it yet.

385
00:28:05,683 --> 00:28:07,727
(GROANS)

386
00:28:07,810 --> 00:28:09,312
Professor!

387
00:28:09,937 --> 00:28:11,397
(GROANS)

388
00:28:11,481 --> 00:28:12,482
(GRUNTS)

389
00:28:15,443 --> 00:28:16,652
Professor!

390
00:28:18,029 --> 00:28:19,322
- (ROARS)
- (GRUNTS)

391
00:28:19,781 --> 00:28:21,115
(HANK ROARS)

392
00:28:21,449 --> 00:28:23,117
(LOGAN SCREAMING)

393
00:28:24,911 --> 00:28:25,912
(ROARS)

394
00:28:31,709 --> 00:28:33,336
CHARLES: Hank?

395
00:28:33,503 --> 00:28:35,296
What's going on here?

396
00:28:36,631 --> 00:28:37,799
Professor?

397
00:28:37,882 --> 00:28:39,175
Please don't
call me that.

398
00:28:39,300 --> 00:28:40,802
Why?
You know this guy?

399
00:28:40,968 --> 00:28:43,262
Yeah, he looks
slightly familiar.

400
00:28:43,346 --> 00:28:45,556
Get off the bloody
chandelier, Hank.

401
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:47,350
(GLASS CLINKING)

402
00:28:47,433 --> 00:28:48,768
You can walk.

403
00:28:48,935 --> 00:28:50,144
You're a perceptive one.

404
00:28:50,269 --> 00:28:51,813
I thought Erik--

405
00:28:51,979 --> 00:28:53,106
Which makes it
slightly perplexing that

406
00:28:53,189 --> 00:28:55,066
you missed our
sign on the way in.

407
00:28:55,149 --> 00:28:56,401
This is private property,
my friend.

408
00:28:56,484 --> 00:28:58,611
I'm gonna have to ask him
to ask you to leave.

409
00:28:58,736 --> 00:29:00,154
Well. (SIGHS)

410
00:29:00,238 --> 00:29:02,156
I'm afraid
I can't do that...

411
00:29:04,534 --> 00:29:06,160
because I was
sent here for you.

412
00:29:06,327 --> 00:29:09,288
Well, tell whoever it was
that sent you that I'm busy.

413
00:29:10,206 --> 00:29:11,527
That's gonna be
a little tricky...

414
00:29:11,999 --> 00:29:15,336
because the person
who sent me was you.

415
00:29:15,503 --> 00:29:16,504
What?

416
00:29:16,587 --> 00:29:18,256
About 50 years from now.

417
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:19,903
Like in the future,
50 years from now?

418
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:20,925
Yeah.

419
00:29:21,008 --> 00:29:22,927
- I sent you from the future?
- Yeah.

420
00:29:23,511 --> 00:29:24,637
CHARLES: Piss off.

421
00:29:25,847 --> 00:29:28,433
If you had your powers, you'd
know I was telling the truth.

422
00:29:28,599 --> 00:29:31,227
How do you know
I don't have my p--

423
00:29:31,477 --> 00:29:33,062
- Who are you?
LOGAN: I told you.

424
00:29:33,146 --> 00:29:34,605
- Are you CIA?
- No.

425
00:29:34,689 --> 00:29:35,690
You've been watching me?

426
00:29:35,815 --> 00:29:37,483
I know you, Charles.

427
00:29:37,567 --> 00:29:39,569
We've been friends
for years.

428
00:29:39,944 --> 00:29:41,696
I know your powers
came when you were 9.

429
00:29:42,530 --> 00:29:44,574
I know you thought you were going
crazy when it started...

430
00:29:44,740 --> 00:29:46,784
all the voices
in your head.

431
00:29:46,868 --> 00:29:48,411
And it wasn't
until you were 12...

432
00:29:48,494 --> 00:29:51,998
that you realized all the voices
were in everyone else's head.

433
00:29:52,165 --> 00:29:54,375
Do you want me to go on?

434
00:29:55,543 --> 00:29:57,044
I never told anyone that.

435
00:29:57,128 --> 00:30:00,756
Not yet, no,
but, you will.

436
00:30:02,008 --> 00:30:03,448
All right,
you've piqued my interest.

437
00:30:03,509 --> 00:30:05,094
What do you want?

438
00:30:05,261 --> 00:30:07,346
We have to stop Raven.

439
00:30:09,682 --> 00:30:11,601
I need your help.

440
00:30:12,727 --> 00:30:14,520
We need your help.

441
00:30:18,733 --> 00:30:20,818
I think I'd like
to wake up now.

442
00:30:23,779 --> 00:30:25,114
(SIGHS)

443
00:30:25,907 --> 00:30:27,992
What does she
have to do with this?

444
00:30:32,205 --> 00:30:33,873
CHARLES:  So you're saying...

445
00:30:33,956 --> 00:30:36,167
they took Raven's
power, and what?

446
00:30:36,501 --> 00:30:38,711
They weaponized it?

447
00:30:38,878 --> 00:30:39,879
Yep.

448
00:30:40,338 --> 00:30:42,089
She is unique.

449
00:30:42,256 --> 00:30:44,175
Yeah, she is, Hank.

450
00:30:44,342 --> 00:30:47,261
LOGAN: In the beginning, the Sentinels
were just targeting mutants.

451
00:30:47,345 --> 00:30:50,223
Then they began to identify the
genetics in non-mutants...

452
00:30:51,599 --> 00:30:54,977
who would eventually have mutant
children and grandchildren.

453
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:58,523
Many of the humans tried to help
us, but it was a slaughter.

454
00:30:58,940 --> 00:31:01,692
leaving only the worst
of humanity in charge.

455
00:31:01,859 --> 00:31:03,819
I've been in a lot of wars.

456
00:31:05,947 --> 00:31:07,823
I'd never seen
anything like this.

457
00:31:08,616 --> 00:31:10,117
And it all starts
with her.

458
00:31:10,201 --> 00:31:12,662
Let's just say
for the sake of...

459
00:31:13,663 --> 00:31:16,415
the sake, that I
choose to believe you...

460
00:31:16,582 --> 00:31:19,627
that I choose to help you.
Raven won't listen to me.

461
00:31:20,586 --> 00:31:21,712
(SIGHS)

462
00:31:21,796 --> 00:31:25,716
Her heart and soul
belong to someone else now.

463
00:31:26,133 --> 00:31:27,218
LOGAN: I know.

464
00:31:29,095 --> 00:31:31,722
That's why we're
gonna need Magneto, too.

465
00:31:32,098 --> 00:31:34,100
HANK: Erik?
- (LAUGHING)

466
00:31:34,642 --> 00:31:36,060
- You do know where he is?
- Yeah.

467
00:31:37,478 --> 00:31:39,272
(LAUGHING)

468
00:31:42,608 --> 00:31:43,859
He's where he belongs.

469
00:31:44,944 --> 00:31:46,445
You're just
gonna walk out?

470
00:31:46,529 --> 00:31:49,115
Ooh, top marks. Like I
said, you are perceptive.

471
00:31:49,198 --> 00:31:51,118
The Professor I know would
never turn his back...

472
00:31:51,242 --> 00:31:53,160
on someone who'd
lost their path.

473
00:31:53,327 --> 00:31:55,329
Especially
someone he loved.

474
00:31:57,748 --> 00:31:59,083
You know...

475
00:31:59,250 --> 00:32:01,377
I think I do
remember you now.

476
00:32:01,544 --> 00:32:03,754
Yeah. We came to
you a long time ago...

477
00:32:03,838 --> 00:32:05,965
seeking your help.

478
00:32:06,507 --> 00:32:09,969
And I'm gonna say to you
what you said to us then.

479
00:32:11,721 --> 00:32:12,930
Fuck off.

480
00:32:13,431 --> 00:32:14,724
Listen to me,
you little shit.

481
00:32:15,224 --> 00:32:18,352
I've come a long way, and I've
watched a lot of people die.

482
00:32:18,519 --> 00:32:20,187
Good people. Friends.

483
00:32:20,438 --> 00:32:21,731
If you're gonna
wallow in self-pity...

484
00:32:21,856 --> 00:32:23,691
and do nothing, then you're
gonna watch the same thing...

485
00:32:23,774 --> 00:32:25,443
you understand?

486
00:32:30,197 --> 00:32:32,199
We all have to
die sometime.

487
00:32:37,288 --> 00:32:38,914
Told you there was
no professor here.

488
00:32:41,167 --> 00:32:43,002
What the hell
happened to him?

489
00:32:46,922 --> 00:32:48,924
HANK:  He lost everything.

490
00:32:49,091 --> 00:32:51,510
 Erik, Raven...

491
00:32:51,677 --> 00:32:53,471
 his legs.

492
00:32:53,638 --> 00:32:56,515
(SIGHS)  We built the school,
the labs, this whole place...

493
00:32:56,724 --> 00:33:00,436
then, just after
the first semester...

494
00:33:00,603 --> 00:33:02,188
the war in Vietnam
got worse.

495
00:33:03,272 --> 00:33:04,774
Many of the teachers...

496
00:33:05,191 --> 00:33:07,777
and older students
were drafted.

497
00:33:08,152 --> 00:33:09,487
It broke him.

498
00:33:09,945 --> 00:33:12,281
 He retreated into himself.

499
00:33:12,448 --> 00:33:14,700
 I wanted to help,
do something...

500
00:33:14,867 --> 00:33:16,911
 so I designed a serum
to treat his spine...

501
00:33:17,078 --> 00:33:21,123
 derived from the same formula that
helps me control my mutation.

502
00:33:22,375 --> 00:33:25,086
(SIGHS) I take just enough
to keep myself balanced...

503
00:33:26,754 --> 00:33:28,214
but he takes too much.

504
00:33:28,631 --> 00:33:30,633
I tried easing him back...

505
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:34,303
but he just couldn't bear
the pain, the voices.

506
00:33:34,470 --> 00:33:36,931
The treatment
gives him his legs...

507
00:33:37,682 --> 00:33:39,600
but it's not enough.

508
00:33:39,809 --> 00:33:40,810
He's...

509
00:33:43,437 --> 00:33:45,106
He's just lost too much.

510
00:33:47,650 --> 00:33:49,026
(SIGHS)

511
00:33:58,327 --> 00:33:59,954
YOUNG RAVEN:  You're
not scared of me?

512
00:34:00,830 --> 00:34:04,041
YOUNG CHARLES:  I always believed I
couldn't be the only one in the world.

513
00:34:04,917 --> 00:34:06,085
 Charles Xavier.

514
00:34:08,796 --> 00:34:09,964
Raven.

515
00:34:11,340 --> 00:34:13,050
You're hungry and alone.

516
00:34:13,426 --> 00:34:14,885
Take whatever you want.

517
00:34:14,969 --> 00:34:17,888
We've got lots of food.
You don't have to steal.

518
00:34:18,889 --> 00:34:20,099
In fact...

519
00:34:20,266 --> 00:34:22,768
 you never have to
steal again.

520
00:34:23,102 --> 00:34:25,104
 And that's a promise.

521
00:34:30,651 --> 00:34:32,695
CHARLES: I'll
help you get her.

522
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:37,575
Not for any of your future
shite, but for her.

523
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:38,909
Fair enough.

524
00:34:40,077 --> 00:34:42,204
But I'll tell you this.
You don't know Erik.

525
00:34:42,413 --> 00:34:44,999
That man is a monster.
A murderer.

526
00:34:45,124 --> 00:34:47,877
You think you can
convince Raven to change?

527
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:49,086
To come home?

528
00:34:49,503 --> 00:34:50,921
That's splendid.

529
00:34:51,797 --> 00:34:54,341
But what makes you think
you can change him?

530
00:34:54,508 --> 00:34:58,095
Because you and Erik sent
me back here together.

531
00:35:00,931 --> 00:35:02,433
HANK:  The room
they're holding him in

532
00:35:02,516 --> 00:35:03,809
 was built during
the Second World War...

533
00:35:03,976 --> 00:35:05,519
 when there was
a shortage of steel.

534
00:35:05,603 --> 00:35:09,440
 So the foundation is pure
concrete and sand. No metal.

535
00:35:09,607 --> 00:35:10,691
CHARLES:
He's being held...

536
00:35:10,858 --> 00:35:13,068
a hundred floors
beneath the most

537
00:35:13,194 --> 00:35:15,446
heavily guarded
building on the planet.

538
00:35:15,613 --> 00:35:16,989
LOGAN: Why is he in there?

539
00:35:18,699 --> 00:35:19,950
What, he forgot
to mention?

540
00:35:20,910 --> 00:35:21,911
(SNICKERING)

541
00:35:22,119 --> 00:35:23,162
Uh, JFK.

542
00:35:23,579 --> 00:35:24,622
He killed--

543
00:35:24,705 --> 00:35:25,873
(CHUCKLING)

544
00:35:25,956 --> 00:35:29,627
What else explains a bullet
miraculously curving through the air?

545
00:35:29,794 --> 00:35:31,420
Erik's always had
a way with guns.

546
00:35:31,545 --> 00:35:33,265
Are you sure you want
to carry on with this?

547
00:35:33,297 --> 00:35:34,673
This is your plan,
not mine.

548
00:35:34,757 --> 00:35:36,842
HANK: We don't have any
resources to get us in.

549
00:35:36,926 --> 00:35:38,594
CHARLES: Or out.

550
00:35:39,220 --> 00:35:40,846
It's just me and Hank.

551
00:35:41,013 --> 00:35:42,348
I knew a guy.

552
00:35:42,556 --> 00:35:43,974
Yeah, he'd be
a young man now.

553
00:35:44,099 --> 00:35:47,394
Grew up outside of D.C.
(CHUCKLING)

554
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:49,104
He could get
into anywhere.

555
00:35:49,271 --> 00:35:51,816
I just don't know how the hell
we're gonna find him.

556
00:35:53,150 --> 00:35:55,820
Is Cerebro out
of the question?

557
00:35:58,405 --> 00:36:00,616
We have a phonebook.

558
00:36:06,956 --> 00:36:09,250
I thought you'd be getting
ready for your trip, sir.

559
00:36:09,416 --> 00:36:11,293
I just came to
grab a couple files.

560
00:36:11,460 --> 00:36:14,880
Is that a new scarf?
It's nice.

561
00:36:15,047 --> 00:36:16,131
Thank you.

562
00:37:03,554 --> 00:37:04,555
(BEEPS)

563
00:37:37,546 --> 00:37:38,672
(BREATH TREMBLING)

564
00:37:40,925 --> 00:37:42,009
(GASPS)

565
00:37:47,431 --> 00:37:48,682
Dr. Trask?

566
00:37:48,766 --> 00:37:49,850
One second.

567
00:37:50,935 --> 00:37:52,102
Oh.

568
00:37:52,186 --> 00:37:54,688
We added some names
to the Paris meeting.

569
00:37:58,192 --> 00:37:59,443
Thank you.

570
00:38:00,611 --> 00:38:01,946
Is something wrong, sir?

571
00:38:02,905 --> 00:38:05,032
No. It's nothing.

572
00:38:05,366 --> 00:38:07,952
Would you mind
typing up my itinerary?

573
00:38:08,577 --> 00:38:10,120
I don't wanna
miss anything.

574
00:38:18,420 --> 00:38:19,981
LOGAN: Here, here, here.
CHARLES: Where?

575
00:38:20,005 --> 00:38:21,423
- Just stop here.
- All right, all right.

576
00:38:21,590 --> 00:38:23,717
Next time I'm driving.
Don't get used to it.

577
00:38:28,847 --> 00:38:29,848
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

578
00:38:30,808 --> 00:38:31,976
(MAN TALKING ON TV)

579
00:38:41,402 --> 00:38:43,195
(SIGHS)
What's he done now?

580
00:38:43,278 --> 00:38:45,030
I will just write you a
check for whatever he took.

581
00:38:45,197 --> 00:38:46,448
We just need
to talk to him.

582
00:38:48,993 --> 00:38:53,330
Peter! The cops
are here. Again.

583
00:38:53,414 --> 00:38:55,499
- (ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)
- (PLAYING PING-PONG)

584
00:39:00,379 --> 00:39:01,500
PETER: What do
you guys want?

585
00:39:01,630 --> 00:39:04,299
I didn't do anything.
I've been here all day.

586
00:39:05,426 --> 00:39:07,386
Just relax, Peter.
We're not cops.

587
00:39:07,553 --> 00:39:08,595
Of course you're not.
If you were,

588
00:39:08,679 --> 00:39:09,763
you wouldn't be
driving a rental car.

589
00:39:09,930 --> 00:39:10,931
How did you know
we've got a rental car?

590
00:39:11,056 --> 00:39:12,933
I checked your registration when
you were walking to the door.

591
00:39:13,058 --> 00:39:14,018
I also had
some time to kill

592
00:39:14,101 --> 00:39:15,102
so I went through
your rental agreement.

593
00:39:15,269 --> 00:39:17,354
Saw you were from out of town.
Are you FBI?

594
00:39:18,313 --> 00:39:20,441
No, you're not cops. Hey, what's
with this gifted youngsters place?

595
00:39:20,607 --> 00:39:22,943
That's an old card.

596
00:39:24,194 --> 00:39:26,196
- He's fascinating.
- He's a pain in the arse.

597
00:39:26,363 --> 00:39:27,531
What, a teleporter?

598
00:39:27,698 --> 00:39:28,782
No, he's just fast.

599
00:39:28,907 --> 00:39:31,326
And when I knew him
he wasn't so... young.

600
00:39:32,161 --> 00:39:33,996
PETER: Young?
You're just old.

601
00:39:34,997 --> 00:39:36,874
So you're not afraid
to show your powers?

602
00:39:37,041 --> 00:39:38,602
What powers? What
are you talking about?

603
00:39:39,376 --> 00:39:40,836
Do you see
something strange here?

604
00:39:42,004 --> 00:39:44,131
Nothing anybody would
believe if you told them.

605
00:39:46,967 --> 00:39:48,177
(ARCADE GAME PINGING)

606
00:39:48,260 --> 00:39:49,803
So, who are you?
What do you want?

607
00:39:49,887 --> 00:39:51,607
LOGAN: We need your help, Peter.
- For what?

608
00:39:51,722 --> 00:39:53,766
To break into a highly
secured facility...

609
00:39:54,183 --> 00:39:55,476
and to get someone out.

610
00:39:55,642 --> 00:39:56,685
Prison break?

611
00:39:57,352 --> 00:39:58,520
That's illegal, you know.

612
00:39:58,812 --> 00:39:59,813
Um...

613
00:40:02,900 --> 00:40:04,735
Well, only if
you get caught.

614
00:40:04,902 --> 00:40:05,944
So, what's in it for me?

615
00:40:06,028 --> 00:40:09,406
You, you kleptomaniac, get
to break into the Pentagon.

616
00:40:15,329 --> 00:40:16,997
How do I know
I can trust you?

617
00:40:17,998 --> 00:40:19,500
Because we're
just like you.

618
00:40:21,794 --> 00:40:23,003
Show him.

619
00:40:24,838 --> 00:40:26,340
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

620
00:40:34,890 --> 00:40:36,850
That's cool,
but it's disgusting.

621
00:40:38,685 --> 00:40:43,482
TOUR GUIDE: Built in 1943, the Pentagon is
the world's largest office building...

622
00:40:43,649 --> 00:40:46,527
housing more than
25,000 military employees...

623
00:40:46,693 --> 00:40:48,278
stretched over six
million square feet.

624
00:40:48,362 --> 00:40:49,363
Where's the bathroom?

625
00:40:49,863 --> 00:40:52,282
GIRL: He always needs to pee!
- (ALL LAUGH)

626
00:41:12,052 --> 00:41:14,054
(STATIC CRACKLES)

627
00:41:23,272 --> 00:41:24,773
(DOOR BUZZING)

628
00:41:41,373 --> 00:41:42,624
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

629
00:41:55,262 --> 00:41:57,514
Yeah, we're getting broadcast
signal down here. What's going on?

630
00:41:57,598 --> 00:41:59,433
Damn it, call Maintenance,
get them down here.

631
00:42:10,444 --> 00:42:11,612
(CHUCKLES)

632
00:42:14,573 --> 00:42:15,616
(SHOES SQUEAKING)

633
00:43:09,086 --> 00:43:10,254
(VIBRATING)

634
00:43:20,514 --> 00:43:21,515
(RUMBLING)

635
00:43:32,317 --> 00:43:34,069
(ALARM BLARING)

636
00:43:36,363 --> 00:43:40,158
...fought for and captured the island
of Iwo Jima from the Japanese Empire.

637
00:43:40,826 --> 00:43:42,202
Now, this month-long battle...

638
00:43:42,369 --> 00:43:43,912
included some of
the fiercest fighting

639
00:43:44,037 --> 00:43:45,580
during World War
II in the Pacific...

640
00:43:45,706 --> 00:43:48,292
(CHEF SPEAKING FRENCH)

641
00:43:48,583 --> 00:43:50,168
(ALARM BLARING)

642
00:43:51,545 --> 00:43:53,964
(GRUNTS)

643
00:44:01,388 --> 00:44:03,724
ERIK: In three seconds, those
doors are going to open...

644
00:44:03,890 --> 00:44:06,226
and 20 guards will
be here to shoot us.

645
00:44:07,269 --> 00:44:09,062
I know. That's what
I'm waiting for.

646
00:44:09,146 --> 00:44:10,230
What are you doing?

647
00:44:10,314 --> 00:44:11,982
I'm holding your neck so
you don't get whiplash.

648
00:44:12,065 --> 00:44:13,066
What?

649
00:44:13,191 --> 00:44:15,402
(SLOWLY) Whiplash.

650
00:44:19,906 --> 00:44:21,241
GUARD: Don't move!

651
00:44:22,075 --> 00:44:23,076
(GRUNTS)

652
00:44:24,244 --> 00:44:25,245
(ALL GROAN)

653
00:44:30,876 --> 00:44:31,877
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

654
00:44:36,256 --> 00:44:37,507
PETER: You're
good, it'll pass.

655
00:44:37,591 --> 00:44:38,759
It happens with everyone.

656
00:44:41,261 --> 00:44:43,430
You must have done
something pretty serious.

657
00:44:43,555 --> 00:44:44,973
What did you do, man?

658
00:44:45,057 --> 00:44:46,558
What did you do?

659
00:44:46,641 --> 00:44:48,352
What did you do? Why'd
they have you in there?

660
00:44:48,435 --> 00:44:50,228
For killing the President.

661
00:44:51,021 --> 00:44:54,191
Ah. Wow.
(WHISPERS) Shit.

662
00:44:54,983 --> 00:44:56,651
The only thing
I'm guilty of

663
00:44:56,735 --> 00:44:58,320
is fighting for
people like us.

664
00:44:58,487 --> 00:45:00,364
You take karate?
You know karate, man?

665
00:45:00,447 --> 00:45:02,574
I don't know karate.

666
00:45:02,741 --> 00:45:03,992
But I know crazy.

667
00:45:04,076 --> 00:45:05,077
(CHUCKLES)

668
00:45:05,160 --> 00:45:07,996
Ladies and gentlemen, boys and
girls, this is a Code Red situation.

669
00:45:08,080 --> 00:45:10,082
We are evacuating
the entire floor...

670
00:45:10,165 --> 00:45:12,876
so that my associate and I...

671
00:45:12,959 --> 00:45:14,586
can, uh, secure the prison.

672
00:45:14,669 --> 00:45:16,171
Who are you?

673
00:45:16,296 --> 00:45:17,839
We're special operations,
CB...

674
00:45:17,964 --> 00:45:19,257
FB-CID.

675
00:45:19,341 --> 00:45:22,177
Perhaps you didn't hear me
when first I spoke...

676
00:45:22,260 --> 00:45:24,096
but it is imperative
that you understand...

677
00:45:24,179 --> 00:45:25,722
we're in a complete
lockdown situation.

678
00:45:25,806 --> 00:45:27,474
We have to get you
to the third floor--

679
00:45:27,557 --> 00:45:28,892
(GRUNTS)

680
00:45:34,523 --> 00:45:36,566
Oh, I'm sorry.
Were you finished?

681
00:45:38,527 --> 00:45:39,778
(GRUNTING)

682
00:45:41,780 --> 00:45:43,657
They told me
you control metal.

683
00:45:44,032 --> 00:45:45,242
"They"?

684
00:45:46,118 --> 00:45:47,327
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

685
00:45:48,203 --> 00:45:51,415
You know, my mom once knew
a guy who could do that.

686
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:56,920
I'm sorry, I'm just not
very good with violence.

687
00:45:57,212 --> 00:45:58,797
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

688
00:45:59,798 --> 00:46:01,299
Charles?

689
00:46:01,633 --> 00:46:02,634
(GRUNTS)

690
00:46:03,176 --> 00:46:04,803
(CHARLES GROANS)

691
00:46:08,014 --> 00:46:09,933
Good to see you too,
old friend.

692
00:46:10,100 --> 00:46:11,226
And walking.

693
00:46:11,351 --> 00:46:12,811
No thanks to you.

694
00:46:14,271 --> 00:46:16,731
You're the last person in the
world I expected to see today.

695
00:46:16,898 --> 00:46:18,191
Believe me...

696
00:46:18,358 --> 00:46:20,026
I wouldn't be here
if I didn't have to.

697
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:22,362
If we get you out of here,
we do it my way.

698
00:46:22,529 --> 00:46:23,530
No killing.

699
00:46:23,947 --> 00:46:24,948
No helmet.

700
00:46:25,574 --> 00:46:27,534
I couldn't disobey
you even if I wanted.

701
00:46:27,701 --> 00:46:30,245
I'm never getting
inside of that head again.

702
00:46:31,580 --> 00:46:33,540
I need your word, Erik.

703
00:46:36,751 --> 00:46:37,878
Nobody move!

704
00:46:38,378 --> 00:46:40,380
Hold it right there!

705
00:46:42,424 --> 00:46:44,092
- Charles.
GUARD: Don't move.

706
00:46:44,259 --> 00:46:46,261
Hands up,
or we will shoot!

707
00:46:46,428 --> 00:46:48,054
- Freeze them, Charles.
- I can't.

708
00:46:48,138 --> 00:46:49,431
Hands up!

709
00:46:52,267 --> 00:46:53,560
(CLATTERING)

710
00:46:54,102 --> 00:46:55,187
No!

711
00:47:05,614 --> 00:47:07,240
(MELLOW '70s SONG PLAYING)

712
00:47:08,074 --> 00:47:12,287
 If I could save time
in a bottle

713
00:47:13,580 --> 00:47:18,460
 The first thing
that I'd like to do

714
00:47:18,543 --> 00:47:21,171
 Is to save every day

715
00:47:21,254 --> 00:47:25,050
 Till eternity passes away

716
00:47:25,133 --> 00:47:28,094
 Just to spend them with you

717
00:47:29,346 --> 00:47:33,600
 If I could make days
last forever

718
00:47:34,684 --> 00:47:38,271
 If words could make
wishes come true

719
00:47:39,856 --> 00:47:42,442
 I'd save every day

720
00:47:42,526 --> 00:47:45,362
 Like a treasure and then

721
00:47:45,445 --> 00:47:49,824
 Again,
I would spend them with you

722
00:47:50,534 --> 00:47:53,662
 But there never seems
to be enough time

723
00:47:53,745 --> 00:47:56,164
 To do the things
you want to do

724
00:47:56,248 --> 00:47:58,917
 Once you find them

725
00:48:01,795 --> 00:48:04,130
 I've looked around
enough to know

726
00:48:04,214 --> 00:48:08,927
 That you're the one I want
to go through time with

727
00:48:22,023 --> 00:48:24,317
(ALL GRUNTING)

728
00:48:28,613 --> 00:48:30,240
(ALARM CONTINUES RINGING)

729
00:48:48,508 --> 00:48:50,010
Thanks, kid.

730
00:48:54,681 --> 00:48:56,725
CHARLES: Peter,
thank you very, very much.

731
00:48:56,891 --> 00:48:57,892
You take care.

732
00:48:58,059 --> 00:48:59,311
PETER: Hey, I saw your
flight plan in the cockpit.

733
00:48:59,394 --> 00:49:00,475
Why are you going to Paris?

734
00:49:12,032 --> 00:49:13,783
Imagine if they were metal.

735
00:49:15,201 --> 00:49:16,953
CHARLES: Do me a favor and return it for me.
- Okay.

736
00:49:17,037 --> 00:49:18,371
And, Peter?

737
00:49:18,872 --> 00:49:20,123
Take it slow.

738
00:49:20,206 --> 00:49:21,206
(CHUCKLES)

739
00:49:21,249 --> 00:49:23,126
Where did they
dig you up?

740
00:49:24,419 --> 00:49:26,713
You're gonna find
this hard to believe...

741
00:49:27,964 --> 00:49:29,716
but, uh, you sent me.

742
00:49:29,883 --> 00:49:32,052
You and Charles.

743
00:49:32,218 --> 00:49:33,803
From the future.

744
00:49:48,193 --> 00:49:49,194
(SIGHS)

745
00:49:56,242 --> 00:49:58,411
How did you lose them?

746
00:49:58,578 --> 00:50:00,830
The treatment for my
spine affects my DNA.

747
00:50:03,667 --> 00:50:06,169
You sacrificed your powers
so you could walk?

748
00:50:07,003 --> 00:50:10,173
I sacrificed my powers
so that I could sleep.

749
00:50:12,634 --> 00:50:13,760
What do you know about it?

750
00:50:13,927 --> 00:50:15,178
I've lost my fair share.

751
00:50:15,261 --> 00:50:16,262
Ha.

752
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:18,431
Dry your eyes, Erik.

753
00:50:18,598 --> 00:50:20,266
It doesn't justify
what you've done.

754
00:50:20,433 --> 00:50:22,102
You have no idea
what I've done.

755
00:50:22,268 --> 00:50:23,937
I know that you took the things
that mean the most to me.

756
00:50:24,270 --> 00:50:26,523
Well, maybe you should have
fought harder for them.

757
00:50:26,606 --> 00:50:27,899
If you want a fight,
Erik...

758
00:50:27,982 --> 00:50:29,526
LOGAN: Sit down.
- ...I will give you a fight!

759
00:50:29,609 --> 00:50:30,735
Let him come.

760
00:50:30,819 --> 00:50:32,570
You abandoned me!

761
00:50:32,654 --> 00:50:33,863
You took her away...

762
00:50:33,947 --> 00:50:35,031
and you abandoned me!

763
00:50:35,198 --> 00:50:36,616
Angel.

764
00:50:36,950 --> 00:50:38,284
Azazel.

765
00:50:38,952 --> 00:50:40,787
Emma.

766
00:50:40,954 --> 00:50:42,330
Banshee.

767
00:50:43,289 --> 00:50:44,958
Mutant brothers
and sisters...

768
00:50:45,125 --> 00:50:46,584
all dead!

769
00:50:48,837 --> 00:50:50,547
- (GRUNTS)
- Countless others...

770
00:50:50,630 --> 00:50:51,673
experimented on.

771
00:50:51,756 --> 00:50:52,799
Butchered!

772
00:50:52,882 --> 00:50:53,883
Erik!

773
00:50:53,967 --> 00:50:55,093
Where were you, Charles?

774
00:50:55,468 --> 00:50:57,762
We were supposed
to protect them!

775
00:50:58,304 --> 00:51:00,640
Where were you when your
own people needed you?

776
00:51:00,807 --> 00:51:02,892
Hiding! You and Hank!

777
00:51:03,309 --> 00:51:05,061
Pretending to be
something you're not!

778
00:51:05,645 --> 00:51:07,021
Erik!

779
00:51:08,857 --> 00:51:11,401
You abandoned us all.

780
00:51:18,992 --> 00:51:19,993
(SIGHING)

781
00:51:21,995 --> 00:51:23,997
(PANTING)

782
00:51:31,546 --> 00:51:33,757
So, you were
always an asshole.

783
00:51:35,216 --> 00:51:36,259
(SCOFFS)

784
00:51:36,342 --> 00:51:38,887
I take it we're best
buddies in the future.

785
00:51:38,970 --> 00:51:39,971
(CHUCKLES)

786
00:51:40,513 --> 00:51:41,890
I spent a lot of years

787
00:51:41,973 --> 00:51:43,683
trying to bring
you down, bub.

788
00:51:44,267 --> 00:51:46,019
How does that
work out for you?

789
00:51:46,186 --> 00:51:47,896
You're like me.

790
00:51:49,063 --> 00:51:50,815
You're a survivor.

791
00:51:54,903 --> 00:51:56,264
Do you wanna pick
all that shit up?

792
00:51:58,323 --> 00:52:00,617
(FRENCH DISCO MUSIC PLAYING)

793
00:52:01,618 --> 00:52:03,286
(ALL LAUGHING)

794
00:52:09,250 --> 00:52:10,418
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

795
00:52:12,420 --> 00:52:13,421
(LAUGHS)

796
00:52:13,755 --> 00:52:14,964
(SPEAKING VIETNAMESE)

797
00:52:15,048 --> 00:52:19,594
General, maybe you should slow down,
we have a big day tomorrow.

798
00:52:20,553 --> 00:52:23,398
We're celebrating, captain.
It's not every day you win a war,

799
00:52:23,411 --> 00:52:26,267
let alone against
the American devils.

800
00:52:28,478 --> 00:52:30,104
I'm getting another bottle.

801
00:52:46,079 --> 00:52:47,080
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

802
00:52:47,163 --> 00:52:48,206
Excuse me.

803
00:52:48,289 --> 00:52:49,332
(SPEAKING VIETNAMESE)

804
00:52:49,415 --> 00:52:51,376
I'm pretty sure it was my fault.

805
00:52:51,751 --> 00:52:53,169
You speak Vietnamese.

806
00:52:53,419 --> 00:52:54,504
I'm an interpreter.

807
00:52:56,506 --> 00:52:59,008
I speak many tongues.

808
00:52:59,759 --> 00:53:01,928
Let me buy you another drink...

809
00:53:02,262 --> 00:53:04,347
unless you're here with someone.

810
00:53:05,056 --> 00:53:07,392
I'm alone.

811
00:53:07,600 --> 00:53:08,600
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

812
00:53:08,643 --> 00:53:10,937
A bottle of Johnnie Walker please.

813
00:53:24,617 --> 00:53:25,618
(SPEAKING VIETNAMESE)

814
00:53:25,702 --> 00:53:28,371
You're going to the Summit tomorrow?

815
00:53:33,459 --> 00:53:38,464
A pretty girl interested in politics...

816
00:53:38,548 --> 00:53:41,134
Looks can be deceiving.

817
00:53:41,551 --> 00:53:43,011
Lady.

818
00:53:43,803 --> 00:53:47,015
Show me more, baby?

819
00:53:48,808 --> 00:53:51,394
Clothes off?

820
00:54:03,865 --> 00:54:07,869
What's the matter, baby? You don't
think I look pretty like this?

821
00:54:08,703 --> 00:54:09,704
(GRUNTS)

822
00:54:09,787 --> 00:54:10,788
(GLASS SHATTERS)

823
00:54:10,914 --> 00:54:12,665
(CHOKING)

824
00:54:14,208 --> 00:54:15,209
(GASPING)

825
00:54:33,937 --> 00:54:35,688
- (SQUEAKING)
- (GASPING)

826
00:54:37,774 --> 00:54:39,692
(SNORING)

827
00:54:54,415 --> 00:54:57,210
Fancy a game?
It's been a while.

828
00:54:57,377 --> 00:54:59,045
I'm not in the mood
for games, thank you.

829
00:55:05,927 --> 00:55:08,846
ERIK: I haven't had
a real sip in ten years.

830
00:55:12,433 --> 00:55:13,559
(SIGHS)

831
00:55:16,771 --> 00:55:17,772
(SWALLOWS)

832
00:55:21,651 --> 00:55:22,986
I didn't kill
the President.

833
00:55:23,778 --> 00:55:26,072
The bullet curved, Erik.

834
00:55:26,239 --> 00:55:27,740
Because I was
trying to save him.

835
00:55:29,283 --> 00:55:30,827
They took me out
before I could.

836
00:55:30,994 --> 00:55:32,036
Why would you
try and save him?

837
00:55:32,120 --> 00:55:34,747
Because he was one of us.

838
00:55:38,501 --> 00:55:39,669
(SCOFFS)

839
00:55:45,925 --> 00:55:48,344
You must think me
so foolish.

840
00:55:49,929 --> 00:55:51,931
We've always said they
would come after us.

841
00:55:52,098 --> 00:55:55,435
I never imagined they'd
use Raven's DNA to do it.

842
00:55:56,310 --> 00:55:57,603
When did you last see her?

843
00:55:57,979 --> 00:55:59,105
(CLICKS TONGUE)

844
00:56:01,274 --> 00:56:03,151
The day I left for Dallas.

845
00:56:04,152 --> 00:56:05,445
And how was she?

846
00:56:07,447 --> 00:56:08,448
Strong.

847
00:56:09,323 --> 00:56:10,324
Driven.

848
00:56:11,492 --> 00:56:12,535
Loyal.

849
00:56:12,618 --> 00:56:15,371
How... How was she?

850
00:56:17,123 --> 00:56:18,291
She was...

851
00:56:20,043 --> 00:56:21,794
We were...

852
00:56:25,298 --> 00:56:27,633
I could see why she
meant so much to you.

853
00:56:30,219 --> 00:56:31,888
You should be proud
of her, Charles.

854
00:56:33,473 --> 00:56:35,349
She's out there
fighting for our cause.

855
00:56:35,516 --> 00:56:36,893
Your cause.

856
00:56:37,685 --> 00:56:40,480
The girl I raised was
not capable of killing.

857
00:56:40,646 --> 00:56:42,148
You didn't raise her,
you grew up with her.

858
00:56:42,315 --> 00:56:44,358
She couldn't stay a little girl
forever, that's why she left.

859
00:56:44,525 --> 00:56:47,403
She left because you
got inside her head.

860
00:56:49,405 --> 00:56:51,324
That's not my power.

861
00:56:53,326 --> 00:56:54,660
She made a choice.

862
00:56:54,827 --> 00:56:57,663
But now we know where
that choice leads, don't we?

863
00:56:57,997 --> 00:56:59,248
She's going to
murder Trask,

864
00:56:59,332 --> 00:57:00,532
they're going
to capture her...

865
00:57:01,167 --> 00:57:03,419
and then they're
going to wipe us out.

866
00:57:03,586 --> 00:57:05,505
Not if we get
to her first.

867
00:57:06,714 --> 00:57:08,925
Not if we change
history tomorrow.

868
00:57:14,430 --> 00:57:16,099
I'm sorry, Charles...

869
00:57:20,520 --> 00:57:21,521
for what happened.

870
00:57:22,355 --> 00:57:23,689
I truly am.

871
00:57:27,777 --> 00:57:29,817
It's been a while since I've played.
(CLEARS THROAT)

872
00:57:32,198 --> 00:57:33,574
I'll go easy on you.

873
00:57:35,451 --> 00:57:37,370
Might finally
be a fair fight.

874
00:57:38,704 --> 00:57:40,081
You have the first move.

875
00:57:54,220 --> 00:57:56,931
 The diplomats from
all around the world

876
00:57:57,014 --> 00:57:59,058
 are arriving here
today at the Hotel Royal.

877
00:57:59,225 --> 00:58:00,643
 It's an historic day.

878
00:58:00,810 --> 00:58:03,062
 It's the, uh,
official ending

879
00:58:03,146 --> 00:58:05,898
 of the United States' military
involvement in Vietnam.

880
00:58:06,107 --> 00:58:08,234
 There we have the South
Vietnamese Foreign Minister...

881
00:58:08,401 --> 00:58:10,069
 with other South
Vietnamese dignitaries.

882
00:58:10,987 --> 00:58:13,239
The Summit doesn't begin
for another hour.

883
00:58:13,406 --> 00:58:14,949
The hotel has arranged
a private room

884
00:58:15,032 --> 00:58:16,576
upstairs for
your special guests.

885
00:58:16,742 --> 00:58:18,703
TRASK: That will be
plenty of time.

886
00:58:18,786 --> 00:58:20,454
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

887
00:58:22,832 --> 00:58:26,794
Good afternoon, everyone.
Hello, thank you for coming.

888
00:58:26,961 --> 00:58:29,589
Congratulations on
winning this war.

889
00:58:30,089 --> 00:58:32,216
Now, I know you all
have hands to shake

890
00:58:32,300 --> 00:58:34,427
and photos to
take downstairs...

891
00:58:34,594 --> 00:58:36,637
so I will get
right to the point.

892
00:58:37,430 --> 00:58:39,682
There is a new
enemy out there.

893
00:58:39,849 --> 00:58:42,351
An enemy that will render
your arsenals useless...

894
00:58:42,518 --> 00:58:43,811
your armies powerless...

895
00:58:43,978 --> 00:58:45,855
and your nations
defenseless.

896
00:58:51,611 --> 00:58:55,489
TRASK:  You will need a new weapon for
this war. I call them Sentinels.

897
00:58:57,325 --> 00:58:59,243
Named after
the ancient guardians

898
00:58:59,327 --> 00:59:01,204
that stood at
the gates of the citadel.

899
00:59:01,787 --> 00:59:03,122
(GRUNTS)

900
00:59:03,456 --> 00:59:06,292
They have the aeronautic
capabilities of a Harrier jet.

901
00:59:07,293 --> 00:59:09,629
Armed with guns
that can fire off...

902
00:59:09,795 --> 00:59:13,799
 more than 2,000 rounds per minute
of thermoceramic ammunition.

903
00:59:13,966 --> 00:59:16,469
But size, power,
speed--

904
00:59:16,636 --> 00:59:18,554
you could find that
at Lockheed or Boeing.

905
00:59:18,721 --> 00:59:21,224
No, what makes the
Sentinels so special...

906
00:59:21,390 --> 00:59:24,852
is the ability to target
the mutant X-gene.

907
00:59:25,019 --> 00:59:26,520
A genetic
guidance system

908
00:59:26,646 --> 00:59:29,190
- that can lock onto a mark a half a mile away.
- (SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

909
00:59:29,357 --> 00:59:32,360
It won't trigger unless it
has identified the target.

910
00:59:32,526 --> 00:59:34,362
With this weapon,
there will be

911
00:59:34,445 --> 00:59:36,072
no human
collateral damage.

912
00:59:36,239 --> 00:59:39,075
If I turn it on, the system
couldn't even activate in here.

913
00:59:39,700 --> 00:59:40,868
(BEEPING)

914
00:59:46,832 --> 00:59:50,670
Unless there's a mutant.

915
00:59:57,176 --> 00:59:58,177
(SPEAKING VIETNAMESE)

916
00:59:59,220 --> 01:00:01,931
There has to be
some kind of mistake.

917
01:00:03,557 --> 01:00:06,227
My machines
don't make mistakes.

918
01:00:06,560 --> 01:00:07,770
(SPEAKING VIETNAMESE)

919
01:00:08,688 --> 01:00:10,289
- What are you?
- (MAN SPEAKS VIETNAMESE)

920
01:00:11,023 --> 01:00:12,775
I assure you...

921
01:00:14,860 --> 01:00:15,900
TRASK: No, don't shoot it.

922
01:00:16,529 --> 01:00:17,780
I assure you,

923
01:00:17,863 --> 01:00:19,383
I don't know what
you're talking about.

924
01:00:19,448 --> 01:00:20,950
(SPEAKING VIETNAMESE)

925
01:00:27,999 --> 01:00:29,583
(GRUNTING)

926
01:00:53,816 --> 01:00:54,859
ERIK: Raven!

927
01:00:57,903 --> 01:00:59,280
(GRUNTS)

928
01:01:00,281 --> 01:01:02,158
Raven? Raven!

929
01:01:03,909 --> 01:01:05,536
(SHUDDERING)

930
01:01:06,245 --> 01:01:07,580
Raven?

931
01:01:07,663 --> 01:01:08,998
(BEEPING)

932
01:01:09,749 --> 01:01:10,916
Charles?

933
01:01:11,083 --> 01:01:13,336
We've come for you,
Erik and I.

934
01:01:13,502 --> 01:01:14,503
Together.

935
01:01:15,504 --> 01:01:17,673
RAVEN: I never thought
I'd see you again.

936
01:01:17,840 --> 01:01:20,092
CHARLES: I made you
a promise a long time ago

937
01:01:20,176 --> 01:01:21,302
that I would protect you.

938
01:01:22,053 --> 01:01:23,596
(GRUNTING)

939
01:01:29,060 --> 01:01:30,102
MAN:  Wolverine!

940
01:01:30,353 --> 01:01:31,937
(GASPING)

941
01:01:34,315 --> 01:01:35,524
CHARLES: I'm going
to keep you safe.

942
01:01:35,691 --> 01:01:37,318
I'm going to keep you
out of their hands.

943
01:01:41,280 --> 01:01:42,615
Erik?

944
01:01:43,783 --> 01:01:45,951
Erik?
What are you doing?

945
01:01:47,620 --> 01:01:49,163
Securing our future.

946
01:01:49,872 --> 01:01:51,290
Forgive me,
Mystique.

947
01:01:51,665 --> 01:01:54,126
As long as you're out
there, we'll never be safe.

948
01:01:55,294 --> 01:01:56,420
Erik...

949
01:01:56,504 --> 01:01:58,506
Use your power,
Charles. Stop him.

950
01:01:58,672 --> 01:01:59,799
He can't.

951
01:02:22,405 --> 01:02:23,989
(CROWD GASPING)

952
01:02:27,535 --> 01:02:28,869
(GROANING)

953
01:02:30,663 --> 01:02:32,164
KITTY: He's slipping back.

954
01:02:32,331 --> 01:02:33,541
I'm losing him.

955
01:02:37,420 --> 01:02:38,754
(PANTING)

956
01:02:41,048 --> 01:02:42,466
(GRUNTING)

957
01:02:56,021 --> 01:02:57,606
(CROWD EXCLAIMING)

958
01:03:05,865 --> 01:03:07,116
(ALL GASPING)

959
01:03:15,207 --> 01:03:16,250
LOGAN:  Stryker!

960
01:03:16,709 --> 01:03:18,836
STRYKER:  Someone will finish
what we've started, Wolverine!

961
01:03:18,919 --> 01:03:19,962
 One day!

962
01:03:20,045 --> 01:03:21,505
- (GRUNTING)
- (SCREAMS)

963
01:03:25,426 --> 01:03:26,427
Restrain him.

964
01:03:27,511 --> 01:03:28,888
(CROWD CLAMORING)

965
01:03:30,764 --> 01:03:32,057
(GROANING)

966
01:03:39,064 --> 01:03:40,441
(SCREAMING)

967
01:03:41,567 --> 01:03:42,568
Erik!

968
01:03:52,745 --> 01:03:53,829
Where am I?

969
01:03:53,913 --> 01:03:54,955
Huh?

970
01:03:56,790 --> 01:03:58,083
How the hell
did I get here?

971
01:03:58,250 --> 01:03:59,835
What? You came to us.

972
01:04:00,836 --> 01:04:02,087
- Who are you?
- Charles.

973
01:04:02,588 --> 01:04:03,756
Charles Xavier!

974
01:04:03,839 --> 01:04:04,840
I don't know you.

975
01:04:04,924 --> 01:04:06,967
- Huh?
- What the hell is that?

976
01:04:07,092 --> 01:04:10,471
Whoa. Whoa. Look, I can deal with this.
Just go.

977
01:04:10,763 --> 01:04:12,139
Stop Erik!

978
01:04:12,598 --> 01:04:13,724
Erik, please...

979
01:04:13,807 --> 01:04:14,934
I'm sorry.

980
01:04:15,100 --> 01:04:16,268
Erik...

981
01:04:16,685 --> 01:04:18,062
(CROWD SCREAMING)

982
01:04:19,855 --> 01:04:20,856
(GROANING)

983
01:04:28,113 --> 01:04:29,949
(CROWD SCREAMING)

984
01:04:30,866 --> 01:04:31,951
(GASPS)

985
01:04:35,037 --> 01:04:37,331
You're Logan, that's Hank
McCoy, I'm Charles Xavier.

986
01:04:37,498 --> 01:04:39,959
You spent the last
couple of days with us.

987
01:04:43,337 --> 01:04:44,964
You're on acid.

988
01:04:45,798 --> 01:04:49,843
Somebody gave you
really bad acid, yeah?

989
01:04:52,179 --> 01:04:53,222
(RATTLING)

990
01:05:02,565 --> 01:05:03,983
(ALL SCREAMING)

991
01:05:33,178 --> 01:05:34,263
(GRUNTS)

992
01:05:34,513 --> 01:05:35,598
Just hold on tight,

993
01:05:35,681 --> 01:05:36,921
we'll get through
this together.

994
01:05:36,974 --> 01:05:38,309
(KITTY GROANS)

995
01:05:38,392 --> 01:05:39,685
Oh, my God, Kitty.

996
01:05:41,854 --> 01:05:42,855
She's wounded
pretty bad.

997
01:05:45,190 --> 01:05:46,233
(GROANING)

998
01:05:56,619 --> 01:05:57,745
(CLAMORING)

999
01:06:30,903 --> 01:06:32,154
(ROARING)

1000
01:06:38,077 --> 01:06:39,912
(KITTY WHIMPERING)

1001
01:06:48,170 --> 01:06:49,254
I got him.

1002
01:06:50,589 --> 01:06:51,590
(GASPS)

1003
01:06:54,009 --> 01:06:55,010
Professor?

1004
01:06:55,761 --> 01:06:56,845
What happened to you?

1005
01:06:58,430 --> 01:06:59,765
I just saw someone
who's gonna

1006
01:06:59,848 --> 01:07:01,433
bring me a lot
of pain someday.

1007
01:07:02,643 --> 01:07:04,061
(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)

1008
01:07:04,269 --> 01:07:05,270
Where's Raven?

1009
01:07:05,938 --> 01:07:07,189
- Gone.
- What?

1010
01:07:07,356 --> 01:07:09,400
We have to get
out of here.

1011
01:07:09,733 --> 01:07:11,934
We want to know if there's
any sort of connection with--

1012
01:07:11,985 --> 01:07:13,320
(ALL CLAMORING)

1013
01:07:18,367 --> 01:07:20,035
 Yesterday,
the Paris Peace Summit...

1014
01:07:20,202 --> 01:07:22,913
 was rocked by the appearance
of unidentified assailants...

1015
01:07:23,038 --> 01:07:25,332
 the likes of which
the world has never seen.

1016
01:07:25,499 --> 01:07:28,210
 Mass hysteria has gripped
the nation as people ask...

1017
01:07:28,377 --> 01:07:30,629
 "Where did they come from?
Will they be back?"

1018
01:07:30,796 --> 01:07:33,716
 And most importantly,
"Are they friend or foe?"

1019
01:07:33,882 --> 01:07:36,885
 That was London
correspondent Toby Elliot...

1020
01:07:37,010 --> 01:07:38,890
 reporting from the
Paris Peace Summit yesterday.

1021
01:07:40,055 --> 01:07:42,683
What the hell are we dealing with here?
Off the record.

1022
01:07:43,475 --> 01:07:46,854
Two days ago, this man,
Erik Lehnsherr...

1023
01:07:47,020 --> 01:07:49,523
escaped from a maximum security
prison inside the Pentagon.

1024
01:07:49,690 --> 01:07:51,567
We believe
that this woman

1025
01:07:51,650 --> 01:07:53,402
is a former associate
of Lehnsherr's.

1026
01:07:53,569 --> 01:07:55,070
They were together
in Cuba,

1027
01:07:55,154 --> 01:07:57,573
the day of
the crisis in '62.

1028
01:07:57,740 --> 01:08:01,410
He was also implicated
in Kennedy's assassination.

1029
01:08:02,536 --> 01:08:03,912
What about that thing?

1030
01:08:04,079 --> 01:08:05,581
MAN: We don't know what
that thing is, sir.

1031
01:08:05,748 --> 01:08:08,041
Actually, we really don't
know what any of them are.

1032
01:08:08,208 --> 01:08:10,753
Yes. Yes, we do.

1033
01:08:11,587 --> 01:08:13,005
They're mutants.

1034
01:08:14,381 --> 01:08:18,343
He has the power
to control metal.

1035
01:08:18,510 --> 01:08:19,762
Last I checked,
that's what

1036
01:08:19,845 --> 01:08:21,346
most of your weapons
were made of.

1037
01:08:21,555 --> 01:08:25,392
And she can transform
into anyone.

1038
01:08:25,559 --> 01:08:28,353
A general,
a secret serviceman.

1039
01:08:28,520 --> 01:08:29,772
Even you,
Mr. President.

1040
01:08:30,439 --> 01:08:31,760
She could walk
into this office...

1041
01:08:31,857 --> 01:08:35,527
and order a nuclear strike
if she was in the mood.

1042
01:08:35,694 --> 01:08:37,279
And that's only
two of them.

1043
01:08:37,446 --> 01:08:40,449
Do we have any countermeasures?
Any defense?

1044
01:08:40,616 --> 01:08:42,868
I was waiting for you
to ask me that question.

1045
01:08:43,202 --> 01:08:46,955
That's an experimental program, sir.
Strictly off the books.

1046
01:08:53,212 --> 01:08:54,546
(DOG BARKS)

1047
01:08:55,756 --> 01:08:58,425
You're telling me these mutants
are out in the world...

1048
01:08:58,592 --> 01:09:01,053
and our best defense
are these giant metal robots?

1049
01:09:01,220 --> 01:09:03,263
Many of the mutants
look like us.

1050
01:09:03,722 --> 01:09:05,891
My Sentinels can
tell the difference.

1051
01:09:06,141 --> 01:09:08,435
I have eight prototypes
ready to go.

1052
01:09:08,602 --> 01:09:10,521
They're built out of
a space-age polymer,

1053
01:09:10,604 --> 01:09:12,272
not an ounce
of metal on them.

1054
01:09:18,904 --> 01:09:20,239
I want to make
a demonstration.

1055
01:09:20,405 --> 01:09:22,658
I want the world to know
that we can protect them.

1056
01:09:23,158 --> 01:09:24,785
What do you need to get
these things operational?

1057
01:09:24,952 --> 01:09:26,495
I already gave that
number to Congress.

1058
01:09:26,662 --> 01:09:29,414
Unfortunately, they
elected to shut me down.

1059
01:09:29,581 --> 01:09:32,167
It's going to cost a bit
more to turn them on.

1060
01:09:32,334 --> 01:09:33,377
NIXON: Whatever you need.

1061
01:09:33,460 --> 01:09:35,337
TRASK: Oh,
and one more thing.

1062
01:09:35,504 --> 01:09:38,924
If we do manage to capture
them, I would like her.

1063
01:09:39,091 --> 01:09:41,009
For research purposes,
of course.

1064
01:09:43,762 --> 01:09:45,097
(NEWSREADER SPEAKING FRENCH)

1065
01:09:45,764 --> 01:09:46,765
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1066
01:09:46,849 --> 01:09:48,267
Terrible thing.

1067
01:09:49,434 --> 01:09:50,811
What is?

1068
01:09:51,270 --> 01:09:52,771
Being born like that.

1069
01:09:52,855 --> 01:09:53,981
Is it?

1070
01:09:54,314 --> 01:09:56,608
Can you imagine...

1071
01:09:56,859 --> 01:09:59,528
Looking in the mirror and seeing that
staring back at you?

1072
01:10:00,612 --> 01:10:03,365
Yes, I can.

1073
01:10:05,617 --> 01:10:08,245
Where do you think she comes from?

1074
01:10:08,495 --> 01:10:11,290
You think she has a family?

1075
01:10:12,958 --> 01:10:14,501
Yes.

1076
01:10:14,668 --> 01:10:16,503
She does.

1077
01:10:19,506 --> 01:10:22,092
(NEWSREADER SPEAKING
FRENCH ON TV)

1078
01:10:54,541 --> 01:10:55,918
(BEGGING IN FRENCH)

1079
01:11:04,217 --> 01:11:06,261
If I see so much
as a screw move,

1080
01:11:06,345 --> 01:11:08,347
I will jam this
into your throat.

1081
01:11:09,097 --> 01:11:10,682
How did you find me?

1082
01:11:10,849 --> 01:11:12,351
You taught me well.

1083
01:11:12,517 --> 01:11:14,853
It's been a long time
since we were this close.

1084
01:11:16,355 --> 01:11:17,731
I missed you.

1085
01:11:17,898 --> 01:11:19,566
You tried to kill me.

1086
01:11:19,733 --> 01:11:21,860
So the rest of us
could live.

1087
01:11:23,362 --> 01:11:24,613
What do you mean?

1088
01:11:25,197 --> 01:11:27,199
We received a message
from the future.

1089
01:11:27,366 --> 01:11:29,284
Don't lie to me.

1090
01:11:29,910 --> 01:11:31,912
I never have,
and I never will.

1091
01:11:33,538 --> 01:11:35,958
Humans use your blood,
your genes,

1092
01:11:36,041 --> 01:11:38,418
to create a weapon
that wipes us all out.

1093
01:11:38,585 --> 01:11:40,003
I was only doing
what I thought

1094
01:11:40,087 --> 01:11:42,047
necessary to secure
our future.

1095
01:11:42,214 --> 01:11:43,507
So what's to stop me
from killing you

1096
01:11:43,590 --> 01:11:45,384
right now and
securing my future?

1097
01:11:46,426 --> 01:11:47,552
Nothing.

1098
01:11:48,804 --> 01:11:50,722
It doesn't matter
anymore.

1099
01:11:50,889 --> 01:11:53,725
They have your DNA. Your
blood was on the street.

1100
01:11:54,393 --> 01:11:55,727
Whose fault was that?

1101
01:11:57,396 --> 01:11:58,814
Mine.

1102
01:11:59,731 --> 01:12:03,068
I've seen their plans.
They're creating a weapon.

1103
01:12:03,235 --> 01:12:06,154
And now they have what they
need to take it further.

1104
01:12:08,448 --> 01:12:11,785
We have to strike now, while
we still hold the upper hand.

1105
01:12:14,621 --> 01:12:16,665
I've seen too many
friends die, Erik.

1106
01:12:18,750 --> 01:12:21,003
I don't want a war.

1107
01:12:21,086 --> 01:12:22,921
I only want the man
who murdered them.

1108
01:12:23,088 --> 01:12:24,589
This is war.

1109
01:12:26,425 --> 01:12:28,260
What happened to you?

1110
01:12:29,094 --> 01:12:31,346
Did you lose your way
while I was gone?

1111
01:12:33,348 --> 01:12:35,434
Are you still Charles' Raven?

1112
01:12:37,769 --> 01:12:40,188
Or are you Mystique?

1113
01:12:43,608 --> 01:12:45,152
Trask is the enemy.

1114
01:12:47,320 --> 01:12:49,364
Killing one man isn't enough.

1115
01:12:49,781 --> 01:12:51,116
It never was for you.

1116
01:12:52,492 --> 01:12:53,702
Goodbye, Erik.

1117
01:13:17,142 --> 01:13:18,810
(GRUNTING)

1118
01:13:18,935 --> 01:13:20,103
LOGAN: What happened?

1119
01:13:20,187 --> 01:13:21,813
- Come on.
- Can he walk?

1120
01:13:21,980 --> 01:13:23,148
He needs his treatment.

1121
01:13:23,648 --> 01:13:24,775
Hank, I can hear them.

1122
01:13:24,858 --> 01:13:25,984
I know. It's okay.

1123
01:13:26,151 --> 01:13:28,195
- Can you make it stop?
- I'll get them.

1124
01:13:28,653 --> 01:13:30,072
(GROANS)

1125
01:13:30,197 --> 01:13:31,323
LOGAN: Hey, hey.

1126
01:13:31,448 --> 01:13:33,158
Pull yourself together.

1127
01:13:33,325 --> 01:13:34,826
- It's not over yet.
- (PANTING)

1128
01:13:37,996 --> 01:13:39,372
You don't believe that.

1129
01:13:41,291 --> 01:13:42,667
How do you know?

1130
01:13:42,834 --> 01:13:44,503
CHARLES: As these go...

1131
01:13:46,213 --> 01:13:49,508
this comes back.

1132
01:13:50,175 --> 01:13:52,511
They all come back.

1133
01:13:57,682 --> 01:13:59,101
Look.

1134
01:13:59,851 --> 01:14:01,520
I'm still here...

1135
01:14:02,562 --> 01:14:04,064
and she's still out there.

1136
01:14:06,233 --> 01:14:08,360
We need your help, Charles.

1137
01:14:08,944 --> 01:14:10,529
Not like this.
I need you.

1138
01:14:10,987 --> 01:14:14,241
We can't find Raven.
Not without your powers.

1139
01:14:14,699 --> 01:14:16,118
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1140
01:14:17,869 --> 01:14:20,205
HANK: I added a little extra
because you missed a dose.

1141
01:14:21,873 --> 01:14:23,250
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1142
01:14:25,877 --> 01:14:27,045
Charles.

1143
01:14:51,069 --> 01:14:52,445
(INHALES SHARPLY)

1144
01:14:58,410 --> 01:15:00,537
Hank, do me a favor.

1145
01:15:01,246 --> 01:15:03,540
Would you help me
to my study, please?

1146
01:15:08,545 --> 01:15:10,297
- Come on, I got you.
- (CHARLES GRUNTS)

1147
01:15:20,432 --> 01:15:22,726
Are you sure
about this?

1148
01:15:24,102 --> 01:15:26,229
Absolutely not.

1149
01:15:32,777 --> 01:15:34,946
TRASK: This creature
is extraordinary.

1150
01:15:36,156 --> 01:15:37,782
Her genes could hold the key

1151
01:15:37,866 --> 01:15:39,910
to mutation itself.

1152
01:15:39,993 --> 01:15:41,077
I need more.

1153
01:15:41,161 --> 01:15:43,997
That's all they were able to
scrape off the pavement in Paris.

1154
01:15:44,164 --> 01:15:45,332
More than blood.

1155
01:15:45,832 --> 01:15:47,626
I need brain tissue...

1156
01:15:47,792 --> 01:15:50,420
spinal fluid, bone marrow.

1157
01:15:51,546 --> 01:15:52,714
Imagine...

1158
01:15:52,797 --> 01:15:54,341
Sentinels that
could transform,

1159
01:15:54,424 --> 01:15:55,675
adapt to any target.

1160
01:15:56,468 --> 01:15:58,595
If I could just get
my hands on her.

1161
01:15:58,762 --> 01:16:00,597
This girl could leap

1162
01:16:00,680 --> 01:16:02,432
the program forward years...

1163
01:16:02,599 --> 01:16:04,476
decades into the future.

1164
01:16:05,810 --> 01:16:07,103
How old is your
son now, Major?

1165
01:16:08,438 --> 01:16:09,522
Jason?

1166
01:16:09,689 --> 01:16:11,691
He's coming up on ten now,
if you can believe it.

1167
01:16:11,775 --> 01:16:13,276
Eight years
from fighting age.

1168
01:16:13,526 --> 01:16:15,362
And how many of
our sons and brothers

1169
01:16:15,445 --> 01:16:17,197
did we just ship
home in body bags?

1170
01:16:17,364 --> 01:16:19,324
Maybe fifty,
fifty-five thousand?

1171
01:16:19,491 --> 01:16:20,951
And how many more
on the other side?

1172
01:16:22,494 --> 01:16:24,329
Never before...

1173
01:16:24,496 --> 01:16:27,499
in all of human history...

1174
01:16:27,666 --> 01:16:32,337
has there been a cause which
could unite us as a species.

1175
01:16:33,338 --> 01:16:35,674
Until now.

1176
01:16:36,967 --> 01:16:38,969
You really hate,
mutants, don't you?

1177
01:16:39,135 --> 01:16:42,472
On the contrary,
I rather admire them.

1178
01:16:42,639 --> 01:16:43,723
The things they can do.

1179
01:16:45,392 --> 01:16:48,353
I see mutants
as our salvation.

1180
01:16:48,520 --> 01:16:49,688
A common enemy.

1181
01:16:50,522 --> 01:16:53,650
A common struggle
against the ultimate enemy.

1182
01:16:54,317 --> 01:16:56,194
Extinction.

1183
01:16:56,653 --> 01:16:57,734
I believe
our new friends...

1184
01:16:57,821 --> 01:17:00,198
are going to help us
usher in a new era, Bill.

1185
01:17:00,365 --> 01:17:02,701
A new era of genuine...

1186
01:17:02,867 --> 01:17:05,620
and long-lasting peace.

1187
01:17:19,592 --> 01:17:21,052
MAN OVER PA:
 Attention, attention.

1188
01:17:21,136 --> 01:17:23,013
 Transport departure
in two hours.

1189
01:17:23,179 --> 01:17:27,183
 Repeat. Transport
departure in two hours.

1190
01:17:33,356 --> 01:17:36,151
- (SIGHS)
- When was the last time you were down here?

1191
01:17:36,359 --> 01:17:37,736
The last time we went
looking for students.

1192
01:17:38,028 --> 01:17:39,738
A lifetime ago.

1193
01:17:43,283 --> 01:17:44,659
(ELECTRICAL WHIRRING)

1194
01:17:45,618 --> 01:17:47,787
AUTOMATED FEMALE VOICE:
 Welcome, Professor.

1195
01:18:08,558 --> 01:18:10,018
(SIGHING)

1196
01:18:11,269 --> 01:18:13,480
HANK: Raven's wounded.
She won't be moving fast.

1197
01:18:17,025 --> 01:18:18,526
(BLOWS)

1198
01:18:21,905 --> 01:18:24,240
These are muscles I haven't
stretched in a long time.

1199
01:18:31,414 --> 01:18:32,957
(GASPS)

1200
01:18:38,963 --> 01:18:41,132
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1201
01:18:46,805 --> 01:18:48,640
(WEEPING AND YELLING)

1202
01:18:52,644 --> 01:18:54,354
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING
CONTINUES)

1203
01:19:06,658 --> 01:19:07,742
(GROANING)

1204
01:19:07,826 --> 01:19:08,827
Charles!

1205
01:19:11,287 --> 01:19:12,372
Charles!

1206
01:19:13,164 --> 01:19:16,084
(SCREAMING)

1207
01:19:20,296 --> 01:19:23,091
- (GROANS)
- Charles? It's all right.

1208
01:19:23,508 --> 01:19:24,801
(PANTING)

1209
01:19:25,677 --> 01:19:27,470
I'll go check
the generator.

1210
01:19:35,228 --> 01:19:36,813
It's not the
machinery, is it?

1211
01:19:37,647 --> 01:19:39,065
I can't do this.
My mind...

1212
01:19:39,190 --> 01:19:40,400
Yes, you can.

1213
01:19:40,525 --> 01:19:42,318
- (STAMMERING) It won't take it.
- You're just a little rusty.

1214
01:19:42,402 --> 01:19:44,863
You don't understand. It's not
a question of being rusty.

1215
01:19:45,029 --> 01:19:46,830
I can flip the switches.
I can turn the knobs.

1216
01:19:46,865 --> 01:19:50,493
But my power comes from here.
It comes from--

1217
01:19:51,202 --> 01:19:52,871
And it's broken.

1218
01:19:53,997 --> 01:19:55,915
I feel like one
of my students.

1219
01:19:56,207 --> 01:19:57,500
Helpless.

1220
01:19:58,877 --> 01:20:00,198
It was a mistake
coming down here.

1221
01:20:00,253 --> 01:20:01,796
It was a mistake
freeing Erik.

1222
01:20:01,880 --> 01:20:04,257
This whole thing has
been one bloody mistake.

1223
01:20:04,340 --> 01:20:06,843
I'm sorry, Logan, but they
sent back the wrong man.

1224
01:20:07,677 --> 01:20:09,095
You're right.

1225
01:20:10,430 --> 01:20:11,931
I am.

1226
01:20:12,849 --> 01:20:14,350
Actually, it was
supposed to be you.

1227
01:20:15,393 --> 01:20:18,938
But I was the only one who could
physically make the trip.

1228
01:20:19,606 --> 01:20:20,732
And, uh...

1229
01:20:21,065 --> 01:20:22,650
And I don't know
how long I've got here.

1230
01:20:23,109 --> 01:20:25,904
But I do know that
a long time ago...

1231
01:20:26,529 --> 01:20:28,907
actually, a long
time from now...

1232
01:20:29,240 --> 01:20:32,410
I was your most
helpless student.

1233
01:20:32,869 --> 01:20:35,246
And you unlocked
my mind.

1234
01:20:35,413 --> 01:20:38,082
You showed me
what I was.

1235
01:20:38,249 --> 01:20:40,084
You showed me
what I could be.

1236
01:20:40,251 --> 01:20:42,253
I don't know how
to do that for you.

1237
01:20:42,420 --> 01:20:44,380
You're right.
I don't.

1238
01:20:46,257 --> 01:20:48,301
But I know
someone who might.

1239
01:20:48,760 --> 01:20:50,345
Hmm.

1240
01:20:50,428 --> 01:20:53,389
Look into my mind.

1241
01:20:53,598 --> 01:20:55,850
You saw what
I did to Cerebro.

1242
01:20:55,934 --> 01:20:57,185
You don't want me
inside your head.

1243
01:20:57,268 --> 01:20:58,353
There's no damage
you can do...

1244
01:20:58,436 --> 01:20:59,997
that hasn't already
been done. Trust me.

1245
01:21:00,104 --> 01:21:01,105
Come on.

1246
01:21:11,491 --> 01:21:12,492
(SCREAMING)

1247
01:21:12,575 --> 01:21:13,618
Hey.

1248
01:21:14,452 --> 01:21:15,453
(SCREAMING)

1249
01:21:15,537 --> 01:21:16,579
Hey, Logan.

1250
01:21:16,663 --> 01:21:17,664
Hi, Jean.

1251
01:21:18,122 --> 01:21:19,207
Kill me.

1252
01:21:19,290 --> 01:21:20,291
I love you.

1253
01:21:21,209 --> 01:21:22,502
- (GROANS)
- (SCREAMING)

1254
01:21:23,586 --> 01:21:28,049
You poor, poor man.

1255
01:21:28,132 --> 01:21:29,300
Look past me.

1256
01:21:29,467 --> 01:21:31,302
No, I don't want
your suffering.

1257
01:21:31,469 --> 01:21:33,388
I don't want your future!

1258
01:21:33,471 --> 01:21:35,598
Look past my future.

1259
01:21:35,848 --> 01:21:37,976
Look for your future.

1260
01:21:41,479 --> 01:21:42,814
That's it.

1261
01:21:43,189 --> 01:21:44,440
That's it.

1262
01:21:46,150 --> 01:21:47,485
That's it.

1263
01:22:02,166 --> 01:22:03,626
(SIGHS)

1264
01:22:16,389 --> 01:22:17,724
(INDISTINCT TALKING)

1265
01:22:35,408 --> 01:22:37,368
Charles.

1266
01:22:39,203 --> 01:22:40,580
Charles.

1267
01:22:42,415 --> 01:22:43,791
(CHUCKLES)

1268
01:22:44,834 --> 01:22:47,211
So this is what
becomes of us.

1269
01:22:48,504 --> 01:22:50,340
Erik was right.

1270
01:22:51,007 --> 01:22:53,217
Humanity
does this to us.

1271
01:22:53,384 --> 01:22:56,012
Not if we show
them a better path.

1272
01:22:56,929 --> 01:22:58,598
You still believe?

1273
01:22:58,765 --> 01:23:01,225
Just because someone
stumbles, loses their way...

1274
01:23:01,392 --> 01:23:04,228
it doesn't mean
they're lost forever.

1275
01:23:04,854 --> 01:23:08,608
Sometimes we all need
a little help.

1276
01:23:09,567 --> 01:23:11,235
Oh, I'm not
the man I was.

1277
01:23:13,404 --> 01:23:15,448
I open my mind...

1278
01:23:16,032 --> 01:23:18,242
and it almost
overwhelms me.

1279
01:23:18,576 --> 01:23:22,080
You're afraid,
and Cerebro knows it.

1280
01:23:23,247 --> 01:23:25,792
All those voices...

1281
01:23:27,543 --> 01:23:32,215
so much pain.

1282
01:23:32,590 --> 01:23:35,927
It's not their pain
you're afraid of.

1283
01:23:36,094 --> 01:23:38,096
It's yours, Charles.

1284
01:23:39,389 --> 01:23:41,891
And as frightening
as it may be...

1285
01:23:42,058 --> 01:23:44,894
that pain will
make you stronger.

1286
01:23:45,228 --> 01:23:48,272
If you allow
yourself to feel it...

1287
01:23:48,439 --> 01:23:50,149
embrace it...

1288
01:23:51,317 --> 01:23:53,194
it will make you more powerful

1289
01:23:53,277 --> 01:23:55,488
than you ever imagined.

1290
01:23:55,655 --> 01:23:57,407
It's the greatest

1291
01:23:57,490 --> 01:23:58,991
gift we have...

1292
01:23:59,158 --> 01:24:00,993
to bear their pain

1293
01:24:01,077 --> 01:24:02,995
without breaking.

1294
01:24:03,162 --> 01:24:04,956
And it's born...

1295
01:24:05,123 --> 01:24:07,500
from the most human power.

1296
01:24:08,501 --> 01:24:10,086
Hope.

1297
01:24:19,178 --> 01:24:21,514
Please, Charles...

1298
01:24:21,681 --> 01:24:25,643
we need you to hope again.

1299
01:24:33,943 --> 01:24:36,404
Find what you were
looking for?

1300
01:24:42,201 --> 01:24:43,494
HANK: The power's
back on.

1301
01:24:43,661 --> 01:24:44,954
Yes.

1302
01:24:45,997 --> 01:24:47,707
Yes, it is.

1303
01:24:49,542 --> 01:24:50,543
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)

1304
01:25:07,852 --> 01:25:08,853
(GRUNTS)

1305
01:25:13,649 --> 01:25:15,151
(METAL CLANKING)

1306
01:25:52,730 --> 01:25:54,148
(ELECTRICAL WHIRRING)

1307
01:26:13,125 --> 01:26:14,710
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1308
01:26:14,961 --> 01:26:16,462
(WIND HOWLING)

1309
01:26:26,973 --> 01:26:27,974
(MOANING)

1310
01:26:28,057 --> 01:26:29,475
BOBBY: She's lost
too much blood.

1311
01:26:30,101 --> 01:26:31,435
She can't keep
going like this.

1312
01:26:31,602 --> 01:26:33,771
We have no choice,
Bobby.

1313
01:26:33,938 --> 01:26:35,273
- We can wake him up.
- No!

1314
01:26:36,899 --> 01:26:38,150
They need more time.

1315
01:26:38,734 --> 01:26:40,778
I had...

1316
01:26:41,320 --> 01:26:43,322
a glimpse into the past.

1317
01:26:43,489 --> 01:26:44,907
If we wake Logan now...

1318
01:26:45,074 --> 01:26:48,452
we may set our fate
on an even darker course.

1319
01:26:48,661 --> 01:26:50,454
They need more time.

1320
01:26:54,542 --> 01:26:55,626
(SIGHS)

1321
01:26:56,335 --> 01:26:57,628
(KITTY GROANING)

1322
01:27:02,800 --> 01:27:04,802
(WOMAN ANNOUNCING
IN FRENCH OVER PA)

1323
01:27:09,807 --> 01:27:11,434
Raven, stop.

1324
01:27:12,351 --> 01:27:13,978
Stop running.

1325
01:27:14,312 --> 01:27:15,479
Charles?

1326
01:27:17,523 --> 01:27:18,608
Where are you?

1327
01:27:18,691 --> 01:27:19,901
Back at the house...

1328
01:27:19,984 --> 01:27:21,777
where you should be.

1329
01:27:21,944 --> 01:27:24,113
I need you to come home.

1330
01:27:24,822 --> 01:27:26,657
I know what
I need to do.

1331
01:27:30,328 --> 01:27:31,537
If you kill Trask...

1332
01:27:31,621 --> 01:27:33,789
you will be creating countless
more just like him.

1333
01:27:34,457 --> 01:27:35,541
Then I'll kill
them, too.

1334
01:27:35,666 --> 01:27:38,169
Those are Erik's words,
not yours.

1335
01:27:39,211 --> 01:27:40,713
Oh!

1336
01:27:41,839 --> 01:27:44,342
The girl I grew up with
wasn't capable of killing.

1337
01:27:44,467 --> 01:27:45,468
She was good...

1338
01:27:45,593 --> 01:27:48,179
fair, full of compassion.

1339
01:27:49,513 --> 01:27:51,265
I have compassion.

1340
01:27:51,349 --> 01:27:52,850
Just not for Trask.

1341
01:27:52,975 --> 01:27:54,644
He's murdered
too many of us.

1342
01:27:58,522 --> 01:28:00,399
Shut her down, Charles.
Get in her head.

1343
01:28:00,566 --> 01:28:02,026
CHARLES: She's
not letting me in.

1344
01:28:02,193 --> 01:28:05,404
I'm barely holding on.
I'm not strong enough yet.

1345
01:28:08,866 --> 01:28:11,243
- (INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)
- (GASPS)

1346
01:28:13,537 --> 01:28:15,373
I know what
Trask has done...

1347
01:28:15,748 --> 01:28:18,084
but killing him
will not bring them back.

1348
01:28:18,709 --> 01:28:19,794
It will set you
on a path...

1349
01:28:19,877 --> 01:28:21,879
from which
there is no return.

1350
01:28:22,588 --> 01:28:24,340
An endless cycle
of killing.

1351
01:28:24,507 --> 01:28:28,219
Us and them, until
there is nothing left.

1352
01:28:29,095 --> 01:28:33,099
But we can stop it,
right now, you and I.

1353
01:28:34,016 --> 01:28:37,103
You just have to
come home.

1354
01:28:38,396 --> 01:28:40,189
I have to?

1355
01:28:40,564 --> 01:28:42,024
You haven't changed
at all, Charles.

1356
01:28:43,359 --> 01:28:44,443
Like I said...

1357
01:28:44,568 --> 01:28:46,946
I know exactly
what I have to do.

1358
01:28:52,326 --> 01:28:53,911
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

1359
01:29:02,253 --> 01:29:03,254
Where is she?

1360
01:29:03,421 --> 01:29:05,423
(CHUCKLES) She's in an
airport, boarding a plane.

1361
01:29:06,132 --> 01:29:07,591
LOGAN: A plane to where?

1362
01:29:10,553 --> 01:29:12,221
CHARLES: Washington, D.C.

1363
01:29:13,931 --> 01:29:17,518
Guys, there's something
I need to show you.

1364
01:29:19,937 --> 01:29:21,731
We're going
backwards in time.

1365
01:29:21,897 --> 01:29:23,899
I set the system
I designed...

1366
01:29:23,983 --> 01:29:26,360
to record any news about Paris
over all three networks...

1367
01:29:26,736 --> 01:29:27,820
and PBS.

1368
01:29:28,237 --> 01:29:29,780
All three? Wow.

1369
01:29:30,114 --> 01:29:31,782
Yeah, and PBS.

1370
01:29:32,783 --> 01:29:34,201
Look what I found.

1371
01:29:34,368 --> 01:29:35,848
Tomorrow, in front
of the White House,

1372
01:29:35,870 --> 01:29:37,471
the President will
make his announcement.

1373
01:29:37,788 --> 01:29:39,957
He will be joined by Secretary
of Defense Laird...

1374
01:29:40,124 --> 01:29:43,711
and has even sought the help of
renowned scientist Bolivar Trask...

1375
01:29:43,878 --> 01:29:47,381
his special advisor
to combat this mutant issue.

1376
01:29:47,548 --> 01:29:48,632
The White House
has asked--

1377
01:29:48,716 --> 01:29:49,884
CHARLES: Raven
doesn't realize...

1378
01:29:49,967 --> 01:29:51,847
that if she kills Trask
at an event like that...

1379
01:29:51,927 --> 01:29:54,305
with the whole
world watching...

1380
01:29:55,097 --> 01:29:57,558
Then I came a long way
for nothing.

1381
01:29:58,100 --> 01:30:00,180
HANK: And there's more bad news.
I saw in a report...

1382
01:30:00,644 --> 01:30:02,205
they found traces
of her blood in Paris.

1383
01:30:02,480 --> 01:30:05,483
For all we know,
they already have her DNA...

1384
01:30:05,649 --> 01:30:06,776
which is all they'd need.

1385
01:30:06,859 --> 01:30:08,986
To create the Sentinels
of the future.

1386
01:30:12,573 --> 01:30:14,575
There's a theory
in quantum physics...

1387
01:30:14,658 --> 01:30:16,285
that time is immutable.

1388
01:30:16,494 --> 01:30:18,370
It's like a river. You can
throw a pebble into it...

1389
01:30:18,454 --> 01:30:21,749
and create a ripple, but the
current always corrects itself.

1390
01:30:22,666 --> 01:30:24,543
No matter what
you do, the river

1391
01:30:24,627 --> 01:30:26,420
just keeps flowing
in the same direction.

1392
01:30:26,837 --> 01:30:28,130
What are you
trying to say?

1393
01:30:28,297 --> 01:30:30,174
What I'm saying is...

1394
01:30:30,341 --> 01:30:31,926
what if the war
is inevitable?

1395
01:30:32,009 --> 01:30:34,428
What if she's meant
to kill Trask?

1396
01:30:35,971 --> 01:30:38,516
What if this is just
simply who she is?

1397
01:30:40,518 --> 01:30:44,522
Just because someone
stumbles, loses their way...

1398
01:30:44,688 --> 01:30:46,690
doesn't mean
they're lost forever.

1399
01:30:48,734 --> 01:30:50,152
(CHUCKLES)

1400
01:30:51,529 --> 01:30:54,198
No, I don't believe
that theory, Hank.

1401
01:30:55,116 --> 01:30:58,119
And I cannot believe
that is who she is.

1402
01:30:59,370 --> 01:31:00,496
Ready the plane.

1403
01:31:00,579 --> 01:31:02,998
We're going
to Washington.

1404
01:32:20,993 --> 01:32:22,494
You all right?

1405
01:32:22,620 --> 01:32:23,662
Getting there.

1406
01:32:26,790 --> 01:32:27,958
(SIGHS)

1407
01:32:28,584 --> 01:32:31,253
Whatever happens today, I need
you to promise me something.

1408
01:32:32,129 --> 01:32:35,257
You've looked into my mind
and seen a lot of bad...

1409
01:32:36,133 --> 01:32:37,801
but you've seen
the good, too.

1410
01:32:38,844 --> 01:32:40,512
The X-Men.

1411
01:32:41,764 --> 01:32:43,349
Promise me
you'll find us.

1412
01:32:45,142 --> 01:32:47,144
Use your power,
bring us together.

1413
01:32:47,770 --> 01:32:49,855
Guide us. Lead us.

1414
01:32:51,523 --> 01:32:54,318
Storm. Scott.

1415
01:32:56,487 --> 01:32:57,821
Jean.

1416
01:32:59,156 --> 01:33:01,325
Remember those names.

1417
01:33:02,326 --> 01:33:04,662
There are so many of us.

1418
01:33:05,329 --> 01:33:07,665
We will need you,
Professor.

1419
01:33:10,626 --> 01:33:13,045
I'll do my best.

1420
01:33:13,212 --> 01:33:14,880
Your best is enough.

1421
01:33:16,799 --> 01:33:18,509
Trust me.

1422
01:33:29,687 --> 01:33:31,522
(WIND HOWLING)

1423
01:33:42,491 --> 01:33:44,952
There's 12 carriers
inbound, 10 miles!

1424
01:33:45,869 --> 01:33:46,954
They've found us.

1425
01:34:04,013 --> 01:34:06,140
REPORTER: Thousands of people
will be gathered here today.

1426
01:34:06,223 --> 01:34:07,641
They've come from
all over the world...

1427
01:34:07,725 --> 01:34:10,561
to witness history,
along with news crews...

1428
01:34:10,728 --> 01:34:12,229
from at least 50
different countries.

1429
01:34:13,939 --> 01:34:15,274
Thank you.

1430
01:34:16,525 --> 01:34:17,568
(BEEPS)

1431
01:34:17,693 --> 01:34:19,054
Can I see your
invitations, please?

1432
01:34:19,862 --> 01:34:21,113
Yes, you may.

1433
01:34:21,196 --> 01:34:22,323
These two are with me.

1434
01:34:22,406 --> 01:34:23,449
Go ahead.

1435
01:34:23,532 --> 01:34:24,658
Thank you.

1436
01:34:31,415 --> 01:34:32,791
CHARLES: Logan!

1437
01:34:32,916 --> 01:34:34,477
SECURITY OFFICER:
Please, this way, sir.

1438
01:34:51,268 --> 01:34:53,354
(INDISTINCT VOICES IN HEAD)

1439
01:35:01,278 --> 01:35:03,158
I haven't found her yet.
But she has to be here.

1440
01:35:03,280 --> 01:35:05,081
ANNOUNCER:  The President
of the United States.

1441
01:35:05,199 --> 01:35:07,284
(PATRIOTIC MUSIC PLAYS)

1442
01:35:07,576 --> 01:35:09,286
(CROWD CHEERING)

1443
01:35:27,805 --> 01:35:29,515
My fellow Americans...

1444
01:35:29,681 --> 01:35:34,353
today we face the gravest
threat in our history...

1445
01:35:34,478 --> 01:35:35,646
mutants.

1446
01:35:35,729 --> 01:35:36,730
(VOICES RESUME)

1447
01:35:38,816 --> 01:35:41,235
We have prepared
for this threat.

1448
01:35:41,652 --> 01:35:43,862
(INDISTINCT VOICES IN HEAD)

1449
01:35:44,238 --> 01:35:47,825
In the immortal words
of Robert Oppenheimer...

1450
01:35:47,991 --> 01:35:49,118
"Behold.

1451
01:35:49,701 --> 01:35:52,496
"The world will never be
the same again."

1452
01:35:53,038 --> 01:35:55,124
(PATRIOTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1453
01:35:58,335 --> 01:35:59,837
(CROWD CHEERING)

1454
01:36:12,057 --> 01:36:14,852
(COUNTRY MUSIC
PLAYING ON RADIO)

1455
01:36:23,026 --> 01:36:24,027
Can I help you?

1456
01:36:27,406 --> 01:36:28,615
No, you can't.

1457
01:36:28,949 --> 01:36:31,368
(STATIC)

1458
01:37:06,570 --> 01:37:07,821
Here they come.

1459
01:37:12,201 --> 01:37:13,660
(INDISTINCT VOICES IN HEAD)

1460
01:37:14,578 --> 01:37:16,338
RAVEN:  This is for you,
brothers and sisters.

1461
01:37:18,832 --> 01:37:19,917
Raven?

1462
01:37:22,669 --> 01:37:23,754
I have her.

1463
01:37:24,421 --> 01:37:25,982
(WITH RAVEN'S VOICE)
Let me go, Charles.

1464
01:37:27,799 --> 01:37:29,259
There. You see?

1465
01:37:29,426 --> 01:37:30,511
Secret Serviceman.

1466
01:37:30,677 --> 01:37:31,762
Left of the stage.

1467
01:37:31,887 --> 01:37:33,013
- Got him.
CHARLES: Go.

1468
01:37:45,400 --> 01:37:47,319
(SENTINELS POWERING UP)

1469
01:37:53,784 --> 01:37:55,077
What the hell
are you doing?

1470
01:37:55,160 --> 01:37:56,578
I didn't tell you
to activate them.

1471
01:37:56,662 --> 01:37:57,829
I didn't.

1472
01:38:07,464 --> 01:38:09,383
(CROWD GASPING)

1473
01:38:16,431 --> 01:38:18,308
CHARLES:  Raven,
please, listen to me.

1474
01:38:18,809 --> 01:38:22,938
 We've been given a second
chance to define who we are.

1475
01:38:24,982 --> 01:38:26,358
 Don't do this.

1476
01:38:29,778 --> 01:38:32,030
Gentlemen, you cannot
pass this point.

1477
01:38:39,871 --> 01:38:41,623
We can't stop that many.

1478
01:38:41,790 --> 01:38:44,668
No, but we can
slow them down.

1479
01:38:59,433 --> 01:39:00,642
(CROWD CHEERING)

1480
01:39:11,028 --> 01:39:12,696
(SCREAMING)

1481
01:39:22,539 --> 01:39:24,207
Erik!

1482
01:39:27,210 --> 01:39:28,879
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

1483
01:39:56,073 --> 01:39:57,658
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

1484
01:39:58,492 --> 01:39:59,493
Ah!

1485
01:40:03,955 --> 01:40:05,290
(PANTING)

1486
01:40:09,044 --> 01:40:10,754
Storm!

1487
01:40:12,422 --> 01:40:13,632
(GROANS)

1488
01:40:15,842 --> 01:40:17,052
(SNARLS)

1489
01:40:23,767 --> 01:40:25,686
(YELLING)

1490
01:40:29,147 --> 01:40:30,565
Go, go, go!

1491
01:40:30,649 --> 01:40:31,942
(MEN CLAMORING)

1492
01:40:32,526 --> 01:40:33,610
MAN: Watch your head!

1493
01:40:34,069 --> 01:40:35,445
(SIRENS WAILING)

1494
01:40:46,581 --> 01:40:47,666
MAN 1: Go, go, go!

1495
01:40:47,749 --> 01:40:49,126
MAN 2: Take us to DEFCON 3.

1496
01:40:49,292 --> 01:40:50,492
Mr. President,
we are Code Red.

1497
01:40:50,585 --> 01:40:51,962
MAN 3: What's our air
defense readiness?

1498
01:40:52,129 --> 01:40:53,380
MAN 2: All our air
defenses are ready one.

1499
01:40:53,463 --> 01:40:54,881
NIXON: What the hell
happened out there?

1500
01:40:54,965 --> 01:40:56,049
I will fix it.

1501
01:40:56,133 --> 01:40:57,175
You said that before.

1502
01:40:57,300 --> 01:40:58,510
I wanted to
make a statement.

1503
01:40:58,635 --> 01:41:01,430
Now the whole goddamn world
knows we can't protect them.

1504
01:41:01,513 --> 01:41:02,597
TRASK: I will fix it.

1505
01:41:02,681 --> 01:41:04,474
NIXON:
You damn well better.

1506
01:41:37,466 --> 01:41:38,467
(GRUNTS)

1507
01:41:55,025 --> 01:41:57,068
(CROWD SCREAMING)

1508
01:42:15,921 --> 01:42:16,922
Charles!

1509
01:42:18,048 --> 01:42:19,382
No, no, no...
(GRUNTS)

1510
01:42:22,344 --> 01:42:23,512
(BOTH PANTING)

1511
01:42:29,559 --> 01:42:31,079
(FEMALE DISPATCHER SPEAKING
OVER RADIO)

1512
01:42:31,353 --> 01:42:32,729
(SIRENS WAILING)

1513
01:42:58,922 --> 01:43:01,007
(BOTH PANTING)

1514
01:43:05,971 --> 01:43:07,722
STORM: Is everybody okay?

1515
01:43:10,934 --> 01:43:12,769
(GROANS SOFTLY)

1516
01:43:28,410 --> 01:43:29,578
(GASPS)

1517
01:43:41,590 --> 01:43:43,174
No!

1518
01:43:46,303 --> 01:43:47,345
Behind you.

1519
01:43:49,723 --> 01:43:51,600
Ah!

1520
01:43:53,018 --> 01:43:54,436
(GRUNTING)

1521
01:43:56,563 --> 01:43:58,523
(SCREAMING)

1522
01:44:32,015 --> 01:44:33,350
COLOSSUS: Now!

1523
01:44:35,310 --> 01:44:36,603
(SCREAMS)

1524
01:44:45,070 --> 01:44:46,363
(SUNSPOT SCREAMING)

1525
01:44:46,488 --> 01:44:47,572
(GROANS)

1526
01:44:56,706 --> 01:44:59,250
HANK: I'm probably not supposed
to ask this kind of thing...

1527
01:44:59,751 --> 01:45:02,379
but in the future,
do I make it?

1528
01:45:02,837 --> 01:45:04,172
No.

1529
01:45:05,882 --> 01:45:07,300
But we can change that.

1530
01:45:07,384 --> 01:45:08,927
Right?

1531
01:45:13,682 --> 01:45:15,225
(ROARING)

1532
01:45:19,562 --> 01:45:21,189
Do what you were
made for.

1533
01:45:26,319 --> 01:45:27,320
(GRUNTS)

1534
01:45:30,407 --> 01:45:31,908
Where are you?

1535
01:45:37,706 --> 01:45:38,707
Ah!

1536
01:45:39,082 --> 01:45:40,125
(GROANS)

1537
01:45:45,588 --> 01:45:47,090
(ROARS)

1538
01:45:49,259 --> 01:45:50,760
I got this! Go!

1539
01:45:57,934 --> 01:45:58,935
(LOGAN COUGHS)

1540
01:46:14,826 --> 01:46:16,036
(GROANING)

1541
01:46:24,961 --> 01:46:26,629
(GRUNTING)

1542
01:46:33,470 --> 01:46:35,138
Oh, dear God, no.

1543
01:46:40,185 --> 01:46:41,686
(SCREAMING)

1544
01:46:51,029 --> 01:46:53,281
So much for being
a survivor.

1545
01:47:07,212 --> 01:47:08,880
(GASPING)

1546
01:47:23,394 --> 01:47:24,687
(GLASS CRACKING)

1547
01:47:25,021 --> 01:47:26,606
(ALARM RINGING)

1548
01:47:27,732 --> 01:47:29,901
(DETECTOR BEEPING)

1549
01:47:35,740 --> 01:47:37,033
One of them is in here.

1550
01:47:37,951 --> 01:47:39,285
(MEN SHOUTING)

1551
01:47:39,661 --> 01:47:41,412
TRASK: No, no, no!
Don't kill it!

1552
01:47:42,080 --> 01:47:43,164
I need it alive.

1553
01:47:44,040 --> 01:47:45,708
(RUMBLING)

1554
01:47:50,713 --> 01:47:51,881
(GRUNTING)

1555
01:47:56,594 --> 01:47:58,221
What the hell
has happened?

1556
01:48:07,730 --> 01:48:09,858
(METAL CREAKING)

1557
01:48:17,991 --> 01:48:19,117
(ALL GROANING)

1558
01:48:22,495 --> 01:48:23,746
(INHALING)

1559
01:48:59,699 --> 01:49:00,867
(GROANS)

1560
01:49:05,997 --> 01:49:08,208
You built these
weapons to destroy us.

1561
01:49:09,167 --> 01:49:10,877
Why?

1562
01:49:14,464 --> 01:49:17,175
 Because you are
afraid of our gifts.

1563
01:49:18,134 --> 01:49:20,637
 Because we are different.

1564
01:49:21,804 --> 01:49:25,141
 Humanity has always feared
that which is different.

1565
01:49:25,808 --> 01:49:27,185
 Well, I am here
to tell you...

1566
01:49:27,393 --> 01:49:28,811
to tell the world...

1567
01:49:29,812 --> 01:49:31,981
you are right
to fear us.

1568
01:49:32,357 --> 01:49:34,067
 We are the future.

1569
01:49:34,817 --> 01:49:37,487
 We are the ones
who will inherit this earth.

1570
01:49:37,737 --> 01:49:40,323
And anyone who
stands in our way...

1571
01:49:40,490 --> 01:49:42,492
will suffer the same fate
as these men...

1572
01:49:42,659 --> 01:49:43,993
you see before you.

1573
01:49:51,209 --> 01:49:53,836
 Today was meant to be a
display of your power.

1574
01:49:54,587 --> 01:49:56,673
Instead I give
you a glimpse...

1575
01:49:56,839 --> 01:50:00,343
 of the devastation my race
can unleash upon yours.

1576
01:50:09,560 --> 01:50:11,729
 Let this be a warning
to the world.

1577
01:50:12,438 --> 01:50:15,233
 And to my mutant brothers
and sisters out there...

1578
01:50:16,025 --> 01:50:17,443
 I say this.

1579
01:50:18,194 --> 01:50:19,862
 No more hiding.

1580
01:50:20,029 --> 01:50:21,864
 No more suffering.

1581
01:50:22,699 --> 01:50:25,076
You have lived
in the shadows...

1582
01:50:25,243 --> 01:50:28,079
 in shame and fear for too long.
Come out.

1583
01:50:29,330 --> 01:50:30,665
 Join me.

1584
01:50:30,748 --> 01:50:34,252
 Fight together in
a brotherhood of our kind.

1585
01:50:34,877 --> 01:50:36,546
A new tomorrow...

1586
01:50:37,755 --> 01:50:39,549
that starts today.

1587
01:50:43,928 --> 01:50:45,221
(GROANS)

1588
01:50:46,764 --> 01:50:48,599
MAGNETO:
 All those years wasted...

1589
01:50:48,766 --> 01:50:50,768
fighting each other,
Charles.

1590
01:50:54,314 --> 01:50:57,942
To have a precious
few of them back...

1591
01:51:06,075 --> 01:51:07,994
(RUMBLING)

1592
01:51:12,373 --> 01:51:13,875
(BANGING)

1593
01:51:32,685 --> 01:51:33,895
(GROANS)

1594
01:51:36,689 --> 01:51:37,899
MAN: Mr. President, sir.
- Stand down.

1595
01:51:37,982 --> 01:51:39,859
I said, stand down!

1596
01:51:41,694 --> 01:51:43,363
You want to make
a statement?

1597
01:51:43,821 --> 01:51:45,615
Kill me. Fine.

1598
01:51:45,782 --> 01:51:47,700
But spare
everyone else.

1599
01:51:59,087 --> 01:52:00,254
(GRUNTING)

1600
01:52:00,338 --> 01:52:02,340
Very heroic,
Mr. President...

1601
01:52:02,840 --> 01:52:04,342
but you had no intention...

1602
01:52:04,467 --> 01:52:06,677
of sparing any of us.

1603
01:52:07,136 --> 01:52:10,473
The future of our
species begins now.

1604
01:52:10,556 --> 01:52:11,641
(GUNS COCKING)

1605
01:52:18,731 --> 01:52:19,816
(BEEPING)

1606
01:52:35,915 --> 01:52:37,250
(GASPING)

1607
01:52:46,008 --> 01:52:47,176
You used to be
a better shot.

1608
01:52:47,260 --> 01:52:48,511
Trust me,
I still am.

1609
01:53:02,358 --> 01:53:03,860
Get out of my head,
Charles!

1610
01:53:04,026 --> 01:53:05,528
Raven.

1611
01:53:05,695 --> 01:53:07,572
Please, do not make us
the enemy today.

1612
01:53:07,780 --> 01:53:09,615
Look around you.
We already are.

1613
01:53:10,116 --> 01:53:11,876
- (BREATHING HEAVILY)
CHARLES: Not all of us.

1614
01:53:12,076 --> 01:53:14,328
All you've done so far...

1615
01:53:14,662 --> 01:53:16,664
is save the lives
of these men.

1616
01:53:17,707 --> 01:53:20,251
You can show them
a better path.

1617
01:53:23,921 --> 01:53:25,381
Shut her down, Charles.

1618
01:53:27,592 --> 01:53:31,220
I've been trying to control you
ever since the day we met...

1619
01:53:31,596 --> 01:53:33,598
and look where
that's got us.

1620
01:53:35,725 --> 01:53:38,561
Everything that happens now...

1621
01:53:39,228 --> 01:53:41,397
is in your hands.

1622
01:53:42,023 --> 01:53:44,108
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

1623
01:53:45,443 --> 01:53:48,237
I have faith in you,
Raven.

1624
01:54:02,460 --> 01:54:03,961
(SCREAMING)

1625
01:55:05,856 --> 01:55:07,108
(EXHALES)

1626
01:55:14,073 --> 01:55:16,492
(INDISTINCT MURMURING)

1627
01:55:26,919 --> 01:55:29,046
RAVEN: He's all
yours, Charles.

1628
01:55:43,853 --> 01:55:44,854
(GRUNTS)

1629
01:55:56,616 --> 01:55:59,243
If you let them have me,
I'm as good as dead.

1630
01:55:59,410 --> 01:56:00,786
You know that.

1631
01:56:01,454 --> 01:56:03,039
I know.

1632
01:56:05,041 --> 01:56:06,709
Goodbye, old friend.

1633
01:56:09,378 --> 01:56:11,213
Goodbye, Erik.

1634
01:56:29,774 --> 01:56:31,442
(HELICOPTER HOVERING)

1635
01:56:41,077 --> 01:56:42,411
(SIGHS)

1636
01:56:44,622 --> 01:56:46,624
HANK: Are you sure you
should let them go?

1637
01:56:47,583 --> 01:56:48,959
CHARLES: Yes.

1638
01:56:49,585 --> 01:56:51,295
I have hope for them.

1639
01:56:52,463 --> 01:56:56,467
There's going to be a time,
Hank, when we are all together.

1640
01:57:00,346 --> 01:57:02,306
HANK: What about Logan?

1641
01:57:08,270 --> 01:57:11,023
(SOFT '70s SONG PLAYING)

1642
01:57:34,130 --> 01:57:36,799
 The first time

1643
01:57:37,758 --> 01:57:38,968
(GROANS)

1644
01:57:39,802 --> 01:57:45,057
 Ever I saw your face

1645
01:57:50,020 --> 01:57:53,357
 I thought the sun...

1646
01:57:53,441 --> 01:57:54,483
(BELL RINGING)

1647
01:58:17,923 --> 01:58:21,177
KITTY: Buckminster Fuller is a
great example of an architect...

1648
01:58:21,260 --> 01:58:25,514
whose ideas were very similar
to those of a utopian future.

1649
01:58:31,854 --> 01:58:34,523
Good morning, Logan.
Late start. (CHUCKLES)

1650
01:58:40,780 --> 01:58:42,448
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

1651
01:58:44,617 --> 01:58:45,951
Have a good lunch.

1652
01:58:46,118 --> 01:58:47,369
- Good job.
STUDENT: Thank you.

1653
01:58:47,703 --> 01:58:49,038
STORM: Very good job.

1654
01:58:49,914 --> 01:58:51,499
LOGAN: Storm.

1655
01:59:22,571 --> 01:59:23,656
Jean.

1656
01:59:25,074 --> 01:59:26,408
Hey, Logan.

1657
01:59:26,951 --> 01:59:28,077
Jean.

1658
01:59:28,786 --> 01:59:30,496
Are you okay?

1659
01:59:32,248 --> 01:59:33,666
You're here.

1660
01:59:34,291 --> 01:59:36,335
Where else would I be?

1661
01:59:38,629 --> 01:59:39,630
Whoa.

1662
01:59:40,464 --> 01:59:42,424
Easy, pal.

1663
01:59:42,550 --> 01:59:43,634
(CHUCKLES)

1664
01:59:43,968 --> 01:59:46,512
Well, some things
never change.

1665
01:59:47,930 --> 01:59:49,515
It's good to
see you, Scott.

1666
01:59:51,308 --> 01:59:52,560
Uh-huh.

1667
01:59:52,643 --> 01:59:53,811
See you
later, Jean.

1668
01:59:57,940 --> 01:59:59,483
Professor.

1669
01:59:59,942 --> 02:00:02,736
Logan, is everything
all right?

1670
02:00:06,115 --> 02:00:07,575
Yeah.

1671
02:00:08,617 --> 02:00:10,452
Yeah, I think it is.

1672
02:00:27,011 --> 02:00:28,220
You did it.

1673
02:00:28,304 --> 02:00:29,555
Did what?

1674
02:00:29,638 --> 02:00:31,640
Logan, don't you have
a class to teach?

1675
02:00:32,308 --> 02:00:33,976
A class to teach?

1676
02:00:35,019 --> 02:00:36,103
History.

1677
02:00:36,812 --> 02:00:38,314
History?

1678
02:00:39,148 --> 02:00:40,816
Actually, I could use
some help with that.

1679
02:00:41,317 --> 02:00:42,818
Help with what?

1680
02:00:42,985 --> 02:00:46,488
Pretty much
everything after 1973.

1681
02:00:51,035 --> 02:00:54,079
I think the history I know
is a little different.

1682
02:00:55,706 --> 02:00:57,416
Welcome back.

1683
02:01:00,169 --> 02:01:01,837
It's good to
see you, Charles.

1684
02:01:03,213 --> 02:01:05,049
It's good to see everyone.

1685
02:01:05,215 --> 02:01:06,717
Well...

1686
02:01:07,343 --> 02:01:09,511
I had a promise to keep.

1687
02:01:10,679 --> 02:01:13,933
You and I have a lot of
catching up to do.

1688
02:01:14,850 --> 02:01:16,352
Yeah.

1689
02:01:19,897 --> 02:01:22,024
What's the last thing
you remember?

1690
02:01:27,112 --> 02:01:28,864
Drowning.

1691
02:01:37,122 --> 02:01:38,374
CHARLES:  The past.

1692
02:01:39,875 --> 02:01:41,126
 A new...

1693
02:01:41,210 --> 02:01:42,962
 and uncertain world.

1694
02:01:54,390 --> 02:01:56,684
CHARLES:  A world of
endless possibilities.

1695
02:01:59,436 --> 02:02:01,563
 And infinite outcomes.

1696
02:02:03,232 --> 02:02:04,358
You kidding me?

1697
02:02:04,483 --> 02:02:05,943
Oh, he's alive!

1698
02:02:07,778 --> 02:02:09,571
(COUGHS)

1699
02:02:10,322 --> 02:02:13,075
CHARLES:  Countless
choices define our fate.

1700
02:02:13,993 --> 02:02:16,453
 Each choice,
each moment...

1701
02:02:16,620 --> 02:02:19,248
 a ripple in the river of time.

1702
02:02:19,415 --> 02:02:21,750
What do you want us to do
with him, Major Stryker?

1703
02:02:21,917 --> 02:02:23,669
CHARLES:  Enough ripples...

1704
02:02:23,836 --> 02:02:26,422
 and you change the tide.

1705
02:02:26,588 --> 02:02:27,673
I'll take him from here.

1706
02:02:27,840 --> 02:02:31,760
  For the future
is never truly set.

1707
02:02:34,984 --> 02:02:41,584
  Thank you for using subs   
    regards, shock

